review: A five star rating isn't given very often by my family. But with this recipe, it deserves nothing less.  Because some of our family are vegetarians I left the chicken out. I used one whole 10oz can of mild enchilada sauce.  The very last thing I did before simmering was add one bag of frozen Quorn tenders to replace the chicken.  I made the pico with fresh ingredients from the garden.  No one garnished their soup except DD who topped it with a dollop of sour cream.  We enjoyed the pico with tortilla chips on the side.  While we have never had Chili's Chicken Enchilada soup, we are definitely looking forward to having your version again!

name: parmesan zucchini
review: So easy so good. Thanks for sharing

name: quick and easy pizza dough
review: Thanks for this recipe.  I decided to make pizza last minute and this worked like a charm.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Fabulous!

name: big grandma s best peanut butter cookies
review: very good

name: nutella hot chocolate
review: Worked for me!  Yummy!!!

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: I loved the oatmeal in these cookies

name: tasty buns
review: Tasty is right.  I made this recipe for my family and we loved them.  The leftover buns my kids heated up the next morning and topped with jelly.  So good.  I will continue to make this recipe.  Delicious.

name: kittencal s famous coleslaw
review: I knew your recipe would be a winner and you didn't disappoint me at all. Excellent coleslaw! I only used a scant 1/3 cup of sugar though as I didn't want it to be too sweet, but so so sweet to my taste. Absolutely delicious.. Couldn't have been happier with the way it turned out. Happy Cooking! THANK YOU!! I can do the happy food dance!! NOW !! I can't leave anything alone! THANK YOU!! Grpa.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: This was great!  My DSs do not eat potatoes or rice so they eat a lot of pasta sides; they like Pasta Roni, but I don't like all the preservatives so this is a great alternative!  I decreased the amount of garlic by 1/2 so they would like it and served with breaded chicken cutlets.  Will be making this often and getting away from Pasta Roni!  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: world s best butter cookies
review: Oh yum!  I made these and we placed an almond in the center and it looked so good.  My family devoured these in about a day and a half!!!!  Thank you for sharing with us, we loved them.

name: bretzel rolls  bavarian pretzel sandwich rolls
review: I was nervous to try these for the first time, my family knew I was making them and I was so afraid I would screw them up.  They turned out perfectly!  As a matter of fact, DS and DD were just eating them plain without the burger in them.  I made the buns, but will try making the actual pretzels next time .  Thank you for making me look good!!!!!

name: adam s ribs
review: We're bbqing at 250 miles south of you, can you smell the temptation?

name: simple baked chicken drumsticks
review: Easy and tasty, I put them under the broiler to make the skin crispy for a couple minutes as that is what my DH prefers at the end otherwise I followed the directions. Thanks!

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: A perfect copy- thanks for posting this!  KFC's coleslaw was always the only coleslaw I liked, and now I can make it at home.

name: wonderful salsa
review: This was delicious salsa.  I used the food processor to save time and so the veggies were all evenly cut.  The addition of the tomato sauce and paste made this the best.  We loved it.  I put mine up in pint jars and I got 8 pints.  Thank you for sharing, I'm off to make another batch now!

name: zucchini salsa  canned
review: We were given one HUGE zucchini and needed a way to use it up.  Since there's only 2 of us in this house new canning was the way to go.  When I saw this knew I had to try it and Bergy's  I knew it'd be good.  Well I was right, it's fairly straight forward with clear directions and turned out great - I did add a jalapeno with seeds to spice it up a little and love the outcome.  The house smelled wonderful as it simmered.   I followed your directions to the letter (except for only adding ONE jalapeno) and the spices were all the perfect compliment to this salsa.  I can see so many uses for it - on eggs in the morning, as a dip for appetizers, from now on I'm pulling this one out every year come harvest time.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: I love that after a busy day being a mum to 4 and with left over roasted garlic my mashed potatoes were a hit.  I always keep a bulb or two handy ready for cooking, but never before thought to add them to my spuds.  Thanks for posting!

name: mahogany beef stew
review: Loved it. Was perfect for a cool fall day.

name: eric s easy grilled chicken
review: Very very good marinade.  I wasn't able to let it set overnight, so mine soaked for about 4 hours.  We loved it.  I also used chicken pieces instead of breasts.  DH grilled these and they were moist and delicious.  Thank you for this simple yummy chicken recipe.

name: classic baked ziti
review: Easy and delicious! Thanks.

name: chicken stroganoff   crock pot
review: You cannot get any easier than this one. It was good. I served it over egg noodles. It was very easy to put together. I used bone in thighs, just let it cook longer which was good because I was gone longer than the 4-5 hours suggested cooking time. Thanks for posting Sisty!

name: microwave poached egg on toast
review: As a mum with four kids who has a severe egg allergy, I need recieps that require little cooking and touching of the actual egg - this is great!  Thanks for posting ( and the occasional hot breakfast for my babies).  Such a pity I can't eat them though....

name: crock pot creamy italian chicken
review: Easy, flavorful, and well accepted by all three kids (ages 8,6, &3).  Used Italian marinated chicken breasts from the local butcher in addition to the envelope of Italian soup mix.  Served over white rice.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Well Kittencal you've done it again (as if there were any doubt :) ) My DH loves meatballs with his spaghetti - me, I don't care for meatballs and never make them, but he's been bugging me for a loooooong time to make meatballs for him - when I found your recipe I knew it would be excellent, and it is - even I ate them.  Thank you again for being such a wonderful chef and sharing your recipes with the rest of us.

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: These were amazing! I cooked our chicken in a grill pan and then once done, used the same pan to heat the tortillas, made for some nice markings and they were nice and crunchy. The sauce was just the right heat. One very enjoyable meal.

name: kittencal s 5 minute cinnamon flop brunch cake
review: Like the title say's 5 minutes.  This was good.  I did add more cinnamon to mine because what I did after mixing cake was take about 3/4 cup of the batter and added cinnamon to it, I then added that to the rest of cake batter and swirled it around using a fork.  Came out beautiful.  You must add the icing, it really gives it that cinnamon roll affect.  I can't wait to try it with Jam n Fruits.<br/>I just want to add that since I made this recipe two weeks ago, my 5 yr old Grandson has asked me to make it twice.  I made it 2 days ago and my Grandson did all the mixing after I measured out all the ingredients.  Fun for kids in the kitchen and good above all :)

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: I had some beans I got from the farmer's market that I needed to use up.  I used a little extra butter and garlic because I had more beans than called for. I also used a natural sugar substitute.  They were great.  Even my picky DD said "You need to save this recipe!"  Served with Grilled Chicken.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: Great and simple.  The second time I made it I think I put too much salt in and it tasted like black licorice.

name: buttered egg noodles  best ever
review: I make my own vegetable stock with scraps I freeze so I always have plenty in the fridge. I like to use stock versus bouillon because it is less salty, but that is just my preference. We also like to add a generous amount of fresh ground black pepper to the buttered egg noodles.. YUM!

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: These tasted fabulous! Used homemade applesauce instead of the oil. A little too thin I think, The muffins were a little too moist. Because I saved those calories, I doubled the topping. That was too much topping.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: So splendid! Everyone loved these smooth, silky, tasty bites of deliciousness. The garlic infused the potatoes giving it the perfect seasoning. The Parmesan made it creamy and ooh so good. No one reached to put anything on them, not even butter. It was a great side to a seasoned steak and green salad. We will make these again and again. Thanks for posting, MizzNezz! Enjoy! We did! ChefDLH

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Dangerously delicious!  I had poblanos on hand so used those in place of the bell peppers.  Also added some chipotle powder along with the chili powder because we like a lot of heat.  Very, very good - thumbs up all around the table  :)

name: opal s pumpkin pie
review: All most like Libby's Famous Pumpkin Pie, ?? BUTthe Same as the one on Family Oven.com ?? Thank you for the post here and THANK YOU,,,  Opal For the recipe, THAT IS A VERY GOOD PIE !!

name: kittencal s famous caesar salad
review: Soooooooo delicious! I was craving a Caesar salad and this recipe fit the bill. I made it low-fat by using low-fat mayo and faftree half-and-half. I also used anchovy paste in a tube--one tbsp. full. Initially, I thought that the dijon mustard overwhelmed the taste of the dressing, but after it had a chance to meld for a few hours the taste was perfect. I am dipping cucumber spears into the leftovers as we speak! I will never buy bottled Caesar dressing again. Thanks for posting!

name: strawberries   cream bread  strawberry or blueberry
review: 10 stars!!!  I made this in a bunt tin sprinkled with cinnamon sugar (about 2 tablespoons).  I had no walnuts, so added white chocolate chips - what a winner!  I took this to a friends house, who had bought raspberry and white chocolate muffins, this was eaten first and the muffins left on the plate (and they were from a gourmet bakery).  I got many compliments, this is going to be made again and again when strawberries are in season.  Thanks for posting.

name: buttery yeast rolls
review: Oh wow.  I never thought to try rolls from scratch (ok I thought but was too afraid to try) but your recipe is delicious and doable!  Thank you for sharing with us.  My kids loved them as to the adults.

name: detweiler sloppy joe mix
review: Thanks Kurt.  Finally, a Sloppy Joe that my husband actually liked!  Need I say more? I tried other Sloppy Joe recipes since my original post.  This still remains the easiest and the best!!

name: wonderful salsa
review: Oh, yum! I have made lots of fresh salsa, but this is the first time I canned salsa. Soooo glad I chose this recipe! It will definitely be my "go to" recipe. No reason to change anything (except the amount of jalepanos/heat); perfectly delish as posted. Thanks so much for sharing.

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: Awesome as usual Kitten!!!  I made my first vegan cake and needed vegan icing so I did this with a vegan butter substitute.... amazing!  The only "change" I made was adding 1/3 cup of sweetened shaved coconut to the mix at the end, yum!  THANK YOU!!!  Please keep on posting ;)

name: homemade rice a roni
review: Simple dish that everyone enjoyed. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: I'm adding yet another 5 star review for this delicious sauce. I used fresh ginger and garlic (a little extra garlic), and mixed everything up in the blender. That way I didn't have any lumps of cornstarch. The sauce turned out to be quite thick but was easily thinned out with a little broth. I also used Splenda to cut back on calories. I used this for a chicken stir fry. This recipe is a keeper--thanks for posting!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Really good and super easy, too. I took the advice of others and went light on the coating and added a little dijon mustard. I think you could easily change up some of the ingredients this way using your favorite flavors. Next time I will use less mayo because with a light coating, I could get by with quite a bit less. About 20 minutes in, it started to brown, so I covered it with a piece of foil. The chicken came out nice and juicy. Thanks for sharing this!

name: quick spanish rice
review: This worked! I live in the middle of nowhere in Japan and have access to Japanese rice and a rice cooker, so I wasn't sure how this was going to turn out. While I do wish I had different rice readily available, the flavors were definitely there exactly how I hoped, maybe even better than I dared hope. Next time I'm in town, I'll buy proper rice, but until then, this works well enough. Thanks so much for sharing this!

name: chicken scaloppine with lemon glaze   low fat and delicious
review: Easy and very yummy! Wish I had made more sauce since mine evaporated hahha. We used panko as well.

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: These are amazing!  My new go-to pancakes!  So good I'm even considering whipping up a big batch of the mix and canning them to give as gifts for Christmas!

name: alton brown s baked brown rice
review: This is the easiest way to make brown rice and it always comes out perfect! I love that I can make a bigger batch this way as well as cook something at the same time.

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: Oh my goodness. I had no idea that something this delicious could be achieved this easily. Simply amazing. Thanks so much for sharing this!

name: now don t go  eeewww    before you try this
review: I gave this 4 stars because it was so weird sounding I had to try it. It was good but will not replace PB&J for me (but then, it wasn't meant to) I love peanut butter, miracle whip and sweet pickle sandwiches. It brighten my day. Thanks

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Yum. Family loved, hate that I can't drain the grease.

name: mahogany beef stew
review: We really didn't care for this at all, in fact we each had about a bowl and the rest is still sitting in our fridge waiting to be thrown out. I won't "rate" it since I did use the slow cooker, which is not really following directions so it's not fair to rate something I've deviated from. It was just too sweet and not very much flavor otherwise. Will definitely do a different recipe next time.

name: cabbage for those who dislike cabbage
review: Love cabbage and loved this recipe! Thanks for posting the recipe, I'll be using it often.

name: chickpeas with spinach  greek
review: This was all my favorite individual ingredients, but it didn't please our palate when it was all together.  I did make a few additions at the end to oomph the end product.  My tomatoes fell apart when cooking (assume tinned ones would not, but I used fresh) so I added some sundried tomatoes at the end which was fun.  Also added some sorta spicy black/red olives at the end (like kalamata, but not as salty and a little spicy) which was also a fun addition.  At the beginning of cooking I added 1 mild orange bell pepper which blended right in and was a low cal addition.  Lastly, added some Greek Seasoning.  Oh and I subbed out lemon pepper for the black pepper which I highly recommend.  The lemon is key to this recipe, so do not leave it out.  Thanks for posting, I'm glad I tried it as it was on the to do list for a few weeks now!!!

name: hot german potato salad
review: Excellent!  Loved it!  I had planned to use the spicy German style mustard, but apparently I don't have any, so I used plain ol' regular yellow mustard.  I would never have thought to use egg like that in a potato salad recipe, but it was delicious!!!!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: I love everything in this!  And not to mention easy!  Only used 2 frozen organic chicken breasts since the hubby isn't fond of white meat. Cooked it all day on low & the chicken was so tender & easy to shred. I didn't think it was bland maybe because I used medium salsa.  This is not a pretty dish, but hey, I don't trust "pretty" food. I would definitely fix again.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I love this recipe, though I did make a few minor changes.  I used 2 thick chops, fresh ginger, and fresh garlic instead of salt.  Arghhh, just now realized I forgot the honey which I'm sure would have made it even better; followed another reviewer and made it all on the stove top simmering in a covered pan.  Doubled the sauce and at the end added some flour to make a gravy and served with steamed rice and a salad.  So good - loved the flavors and really mad at myself for forgetting the honey which would have made it even better.  So easy to put together and full of flavor.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: Great! Very easy to make. I added sautéed mushrooms and frozen corn to this.

name: cajun style oven fries
review: I made these according to the recipe and used russet potatoes. These were okay but largely went uneaten and my husband asked me not to fix them again. Of the recipes I looked at this one looked the best. I think its our taste buds and not the recipe.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: My husband makes this at the firehouse for the guys so you know it's good! I made it once at home and it was soooo awesome, much better imho than alfredo. YUM

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: Nice change from the standy recipe on the back of the chocolate chip bag!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: This made a good early dinner for us on this dark and stormy day. Easy and delicious.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag!

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: Contrary to the rave reviews I read, I found this just so-so, not much flavour. If I tried this again, I think I would add more lemon to oil ratio.

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: We thought these were wonderful.  I've made them 3 times in 2 weeks and they are now my go to 'fries'.  The timing worked out quite close - it may have been an additional 5 minutes but it is easy to time the rest of the meal around them.  Thanks so much for posting this one.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Really yummy ...

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: This was amazing. We cooked in pressure cooker after browning chicken, then pulled out once cooked and thickened up in fry pan, easy and delicious.

name: lee lee s famous chocolate sauce for ice cream
review: Great tasting sauce!  Thanks for posting.

name: low carb pizza
review: Very interesting concept, as mentioned before, sort of pizza/quiche/omelette.   We loved the base, rather yummy all by itself!    I would definitely do this again, tasty and easy.  Thanks!  made for Name That Ingredient tag game.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: Made this for breakfast this morning and made just a few minor changes.  Cut it in half as there's only 2 of us, added 1 teaspoon of vanilla (we love vanilla) and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon as I thought it'd go great with the oatmeal (and it did) a nice hearty breakfast that was easy to pull together.  Glad you mentioned that the batter would be thin as it was and I was tempted to add more flour but didn't and a good thing as they puffed up so nice when cooking.  I even used your recommendation on the honey butter and enjoyed that.  It did seem to give it a little sweeter taste than we like so next time I think I'd cut the sugar in half or maybe even just leave it out.  All in all a great, hearty breakfast for these cool, rainy October mornings.

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: So rich, creamy and delicious. I made the filling three days prior to using. On the morning of the day I was serving, I cooked  the manicotti just until they were flexible,  piped the filling in the manicotti, using a zip-lock bag and that made them easier to fill.I kept them in the fridge until I was ready to bake. They turned out just perfect, really flavorful. I added the optional onion and didn't cook the frozen spinach, but did squeeze out as much water as I could. I'm looking forward to the leftovers and to making them again.Thanks for sharing this recipe.

name: stove top tamale pie
review: We really enjoyed this.  Only change was it needed more tomato sauce and I felt the meat to cornbread ratio was off so I will increase the amount of ground beef next time. Thanks!!

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: I followed the recipe exactly.  Baked it for about 20 minutes.  I thought it was too sweet and the texture was a little too dense and dry.

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: We just loved this dish! Even my DH who does not like chicken pot pies had second helpings and confessed that is was actually excellent :) I made my own crust using I'm Pat's recipe #177343 (which was truly excellent), I added peas and carrots instead of the frozen veggie mix and ended up only have 2.5 cups of chicken. I made 2 x 8x8 pies and froze the second one. I think 5 servings as per the recipe is a very generous size. I will be making this again for sure.

name: the best belgian waffles
review: Great waffles!  They were nice and crispy Ono the outside and fluffy inside.  I made 1/2 the recipe and got 3 large waffles.  Made for Tagging Mania Tag.

name: buttery farm biscuits
review: These could not have been easier!  Thanks so much Bergy.  I had to use margarine and soy milk for lactose intolerance.  I made them to put under sausage gravy.  They were great in my opinion, my husband said they were too dense/hard.... could be the adjusted ingredients though.  Thanks for a super easy, well directed recipe!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: These are fabulous! My sister pays top dollar for these at the gourmet grocery and she shares with me. I can't wait to share these with her! I better head out for more sprouts. These are terrific. Like other reviewers I added garlic cloves to the mix and they softened beautifully. I also added 1/4 tsp. of garlic powder to the salt and oil. I omitted the lemon pepper. 30 minutes in my convection oven at 400 was perfect. I wish I had made more. I could eat these the way some people eat candy.

name: cornbread with corn casserole
review: WOW, this was absolutely delicious! I used one tbsp. of butter and 2 egg whites in place of the eggs so I could cut back on the calories a little bit. I also added 2 tbsp. Splenda as hubby and I like our cornbread on the sweet side. I served this with oven fried chicken. So simple to make and will be made again. Thanks for posting!

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Good- and easy, too.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Delicious.

name: eloise s easy sugar cookies
review: This is a wonderful and easy sugar cookie cut-out recipe. Perfectly simple enough to bake and decorate with kids! The cookies came out perfect. I used Sugar Cookie Icing recipe #64015 from Food.com to ice them. Lovely!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: This was very good!  Made as written but only added 1 celery stalk so DS wouldn't freak out... I think next time I will decrease or even leave out the vinegar, to me it was too prominent.  Served on hot dog buns because apparently I was out of burger buns!  Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: This is a great chili recipe.  I did double the seasonings for us.  Will use this often.  Thanks for posting.

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: I would have done 3stars but my husband liked them more than me. I feel they are too dense not light and fluffy, they are like a hockey puck. My husband liked that about them he said they were kind of like a meal. I did add an extra 1tsp of vanilla and I used sour cream for part of the milk, I think I did 1/2 cup milk and 1cup sour cream that I just folded in. The kids of course still liked them.

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: I've never been impressed with Ratatouille but I thought I would give it one more chance.  It just isn't for me.  It is edible, but not something I would get excited about.

name: bacardi rum cake
review: Almost forgot - I cool the cake a few minutes in the bundt pan & then pour glaze into pan and let the cake soak it all up over an hour or so. Easy and no sticking!

name: bacon wrapped chicken  oamc
review: It was ok. Some liked them, others didn't.  Doubt I'll be making them again.

name: pineapple black bean enchiladas
review: One of the best recipes I've tried this year. Only change I made was reduced cilantro to 2 T (not a big fan). This has great flavor, very filling and healthy. Will definitely make this again. Thanks for posting.

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: Very tasty.  I used low fat mayo and stevia in the dressing.  I also used reduced fat cheddar cheese ... great for a carry in!

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: These are very good!

name: kittencal s scalloped potato and ground beef casserole
review: Not that you need another review on this, but I just had to say thank you again for all your wonderful recipes.  My DH does not eat left overs - ever - he ate this two nights in a row and raved how it was even better the 2nd night - truly a first.  Thanks so much for sharing your talent with us Kitten.

name: world s best butter cookies
review: What almost everybody else said - awesome.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: Used fat free sour cream instead of mayonnaise and use fat free cream of chicken soup I had to add salt and pepper and a cup of frozen veggies

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Quite good.  I wouldn't cook em for 40 minutes though.  30 was plenty for me.

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: This dish is very easy to make and it's totally great for a quick dinner after work. I sautéed some veggies to go along with the chicken. It was quite nice! I also butterflied the chicken breasts before coating them to get more flavors from the goodies. Good recipe!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: YUMMMM!  A very happy family tonight.  Made as directed, if you can believe.  I used all sour cream.  I think scallions would be a tasty addition.  Thank you for sharing!

name: three cup chicken
review: This was something different to do with the boneless breasts I had. My son was pleased with it and said it tasted really good. I used rice vinegar in place of the wine, since that is what I had, and thought it had a little too much tang. I forgot to pick up the basil at the store and then forgot all about the scallions until after we had already finished eating. I made double the sauce and used half to marinade the cubed chicken for a couple of hours and the other half to used per the recipe. I started cooking this when I put my rice on and left it simmer until the rice was done. Next time I would like to try it with the wine, basil, and scallions. (123)

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: These were very good and meaty.  Will make again!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: I love this crust.  I use it all the time for my fresh raspberry pie.  Thanks for the recipe!

name: classic baked ziti
review: So good! Another go to dinner when I don't know what to make!

name: corned beef in beer  crock pot
review: So easy and tasty. It just feel apart on it's own, no knife required. I used Heineken Light cause that's what I had on hand and it turned out great. Thank you.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: I finished a whole piece directly from my glass baking dish after they cooled down. Couldn't resist - so good!!! I have to say that it's a little sweet for my Asian teeth, but when I ate them with vanilla ice cream, they were perfect!!!

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: I am so paranoid by this recipe right now as I have it in the crock pot.  At this moment it smells so GOOD. There are so many good reviews as well as many not so good ones.  I am praying that this turns out good as I have all my 3 children over for dinner tonight and I don't want to throw out 6 chicken pieces with thighs attached.  Here's to keeping my fingers crossed and I will be back for star review.<br/>UpDate:  This of course is not for those who DO NOT like a sweet flavor dish.  I did add some cayenne pepper which balanced out some of the sweetness.  But this was excellent, severed over rice with saute cabbage on the side.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Followed the recipe using Original Bulls Eye BBQ sauce and cooked this the day before.  Put in the fridge overnight and was able to scrape a HUGE amount of fat off the next day.  Tried to reheat in the crock pot but 2 hours was not long enough to get the meat hot (mine is an older model)... ended up using the microwave.  Highly recommend this recipe and making it a day before.

name: fruit salad with pudding
review: I used sugar free pudding and sugar free fruits. I did not use the grapes or the bananas due to a strong personal dislike of both. It was delicious and I will make this again. DH is carb restricted due to weight loss surgery and he can eat this in mini portions.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: This was one tasty beef stew! We even had it over noodles the next day. It was easy to make with simple ingredients. I'll maybe try it with some red wine or beer next time, but it's still wonderful without. Thanks!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: 361 posters have said it all!  Excellent side dish!!!  Made the prep easy by buying a bag of already peeled garlic at Costco.  Made it a snap to put together!!!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: Utterly delish! I made recipe #272116 for the crust and skipped the caramel/pecan topping since I already had pecans in the crust. I instead added a dollop of whipping cream. I made 8 individual tarts using a tiny bit of PAM in the cups. Simpy the flavour of Fall in a pie!

name: turn your crock pot into a smokehouse chicken  smoked chicken
review: Enjoyed every bite! Now that said this is a technique that works well if using most of mamma fishy's suggestions. Started with a small young chicken that was still 90% frozen, after rinsing and drying seconded inside and out with McCormick's "Grill Mates Molasses Bacon". Placed chicken atop a sliced onion and mixed 1 T. Worcestershire Sauce with 1/4 c. hickory flavored liquid smoke and 1/4 cup water and 1/2 a lemon juiced. Cooked on low for 10 hours and sorry no photo as it fell apart coming out of the pot it was so tender.  Cooking breast side down is the secret as it kept the breast really moist and tender. Thanks for the post, we will be enjoying again.

name: divine meatball sandwiches
review: I can't believe I forgot to review this!  I have made this many times and it is ALWAYS a crowd pleaser!  Before you have a heart attack at the calories, realize that it serves 4-5 people (stuffed) so should be a lot less than what is listed.  =)  Thanks for this amazing recipe!

name: mean s dutch babies
review: Yummy!  Easy and fast.  I cooked mine in a 12" cast iron skillet.  Used about 1.5 tablespoon of butter.  Cooked for 20 minutes.  It was puffed, brown and ready.  Had mine with powder sugar and lime.  Also had the maple syrup option.  Fresh raspberries went on top.  Thank you.

name: garlic panko chicken strips
review: Loved these and how easy they were to make.  Served in Sonterra Grill salad with maple vinaigrette.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: So, so simple and so, so good! Garnish with fresh red onion and Swiss cheese. Wow! I subbed half the cream cheese for yogurt. Also subbed onion broth for chicken to make it kosher. Hot peppers work as a garnish, too.

name: old fashioned blueberry muffins
review: Absolutely delightful! Added the juice of the orange in addition to the rind. Good move.

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: I used 3 lb beef, plenty of veggies, same amount of dried dressing mix and 1 cup of water instead of 1/2 cup just to decrease the potential saltiness according to the recipe description. It turned out a little liquidy but the soup was so so so delicious! I also cut the beef into 5 big chunks and coated them with the dressing mixture before placing them in the crock pot. Sprinkled the rest of the mixture over the beef and veggies. When it's done, everything was so tender and yummy! Absolutely TO DIE FOR!!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: by far one of my favorite soups.  I made a few changes to this by using only chicken broth instead of the water and adding half and half to make it a bit more creamy.  This is a perfect recipe for fall!  It reminds me exactly of Olive Garden's version.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Please note that Food.com is not a WW site, and we cannot calculate the points for you; this is something you need to do with the tools that WW provided for you. WW also changes their point system every couple of years, so you'll need to use the current tools.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: I made this tonite because of the rave reviews, and I love Cajun. It was ok.. I did not fine anything exceptional about it. I even followed some of the tips given by other viewers. I won't be making this again.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: I can't believe I haven't rated this recipe.  I have made this a dozen times and always always turns out perfect.  This is my youngest daughters favorite crock pot chicken.

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: I realize this doesn't need 2 more cents....however, additonal praise never hurts! I skipped the freezing step & frosted the cake while still somewhat warm, covered and placed in the fridge. Made the following "tweaks" based on other reviews and/or personal preference or what I had on hand. This cake AND the frosting was devoured in no time. Most went for seconds. I would suggest removing from fridge for at least an hour to let it come back up to room temp for fullest flavor. <br/>Modifications I made: Cake: Used 4 medium bananas (to give you an idea of how many banans);  reduced sugar in cake to 3/4 c total; used 3/4 c. canola oil (in place of butter); used 1 1/2 c. milk with 1 1/2 T of vinegar stirred into it in place of buttermilk and lemon juice. Frosting: reduced powdered sugar to 2 c.; I didn't have quite enough vanilla extract so I put some vanilla beans in the frosting and it worked nicely. <br/>Thanks for sharing, this one is a definite keeper and worthy of the high ratings!<br/>Note: It did bake up well at the suggested temperature and really filled the 13 x 9 inch pan.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: This is really good.  And really easy.  I made this for my family along with some mashed potatoes and green beans.  We loved it.  Thank you

name: baked chicken thighs leg quarters
review: What a simple idea and it tastes great too!  I always season my roasted chicken, but never thought of using soy.  So glad I tried your recipe, we loved it.  Thank you for sharing withus.

name: orange julius smoothies
review: Soooo good & perfect in every way!

name: steven s world famous to die for sour cream chicken
review: These were really good...had such a delicious taste!  I will for sure make again!  I did only use 1 cube of butter and it was quite sufficient.

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review: Really good soup -- have eaten at TFIF Fridays many times, but never had this soup.  It was really easy to make and it had a great flavor.  I did add extra cumin, but otherwise made as directed.  I used Goya canned beans which are very good.  Served with a salad and corn tortillas.  Made a great light dinner tonight!  Made for the Cooking Tag Mania, October, 2013.

name: cracker barrel s hashbrowns casserole   copycat
review: Great recipe! The casserole turned out very cheesy and soft. I cut the amount of ingredients by half to make a smaller portion for two in a 8x8 baking dish. After it's out of the oven, my husband and I destroyed it all at once. Kinda regret that I didn't make more!

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Delicious! I had to use soy parmesan and dairy-free margarine, and it was still pure comfort food. And so easy! Great recipe.

name: failproof french bread  bread machine
review: This was perfect with our soup the other night.  I made the two loaves thinking I could save some for another time, but nope.  We ate them both.  Thank you for this great recipe.

name: easy biscuits
review: These biscuits are very easy to make for sure. I made 8 big ones and folded some ground black sesames in 4 of them. They were awesome! Great breakfast option! :)

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: Delicious pork chops.  I did add some mushrooms to the sauce afterwards, otherwise followed your recipe.  Thank you for sharing .

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: Excellent flavor! I also reversed the amounts for soy and worcestershire sauces. Marinaded for 24 hours and broiled in the oven, 10 min. each side for medium-well done. My london broil wasn't the best cut, but we still enjoyed it because of this great flavor!

name: seared salmon with balsamic glaze
review: Made this last night and loved how simple it was and the flavors of the balsamic glaze was a good compliment to the salmon.  I followed other reviewers suggestions and added light soy sauce, a touch of ginger and a tablespoon of cornstarch to the glaze and it came out perfect, thick, rich and flavorful with a hint of that Asian flavor I love.  Add to that it looked pretty too and you've a winner salmon dish

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: I made this exactly as written.  It was very tender and the flavor of the stuffing was awesome.  It is a bit salty with the soups so I didn't add any extra salt and it was perfect.

name: 24k carrots
review: Pretty tasty ... I did reduce the ginger by half but I will try if full strength next time. Thanks the hubs and kids liked them

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Made this exactly as  posted including the English custard on top, very good - this is the first time I've ever "made" a crumble but not the first I've ever "eaten" one and with all the apples from the orchard decided it was time to make my own.  This was so good with the flavor of the tart apples and the crunchy topping, YUM; the only thing I had a problem with and I'm pretty sure it was me - is that parts of the topping was still dry, thinking I should have added more butter to it or something.  But the flavors, oh my!!  Used recipe#483829 for the cream which was a new experience (in a good way) for me - thinking it'd also be so good with a scoop of vanilla ice cream

name: to die for crock pot roast
review: All the other reviews don't lie. This was loved by all and was super easy to make. Also made for great leftovers today! I realized that the packets of dressing I bought were smaller than the recipe called for, which turned out great.  Made for Think Pink 2013.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: I have a son who detests potato skin, so alas I made this as written - minus the potato skins.  Creamy and delicious.  I was cooking for 10 and put the potatoes and the garlic (covered with water) in a large pot and let it sit for just over an hour - the garlic permeated so much more through the dish (handy if you have four kids and know you'll be running late by dinner time) Thanks for posting!

name: emeril s essence
review: Used this as an ingredient in another recipe.  I made a 1/2 recipe as I don't need the full amount.  I skipped the onion powder as I didn't have any and wasn't making a special trip to the store.  It was a bit salty so maybe less next time.

name: slow cooker macaroni   cheese
review: I am not going to rate this as maybe I didn't do something correctly.  I made as directed but the texture was not good for us and everyone was unhappy,

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Very Good

name: secretly delicious spinach pie
review: I loved this. Great flavor and so easy to make. thanks for sharing

name: delicious homemade egg noodles
review: Oh so good! Froze the extra. Wonderful recipe. Thanks.

name: cranberry feta pinwheels
review: This is a wonderful appetizer Derf, I was so excited to try this that I made it with Greek Pita instead of Tortillas because I didn't have any and I didn't want to wait to try this recipe.  This is so good.  Love the cranberries, green onion and cheese mixture, they all pop, creating something very special.  Sweet, tart, tangy and salty, my kind of treat.  Made for Think Pink 2013.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Just another glowing 5 star review ;) I used Costco frozen tilapia... 5 filets next time I'll make six because my family gobbled it up. Used just a tbl less of the butter and added fresh garlic! Thank you!

name: crock pot apple butter
review: It was easy and is tasty but it's not as thick and creamy as I remember from my childhood. That was a long time ago, though, so maybe the memory is faulty. My backyard apples were tart so I used 4 cups of sugar, 1/2 white and 1/2 brown. Used my immersion blender to smooth it. Cooked about 3 hours on low with the cover off to thicken it.

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: Absolutely love! I cooked the chicken on low for 6 hours and the legs fell off when I was trying to take it out. Never thought that cooking such a delicious whole chicken could be this easy!

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: I'm so impressed with this recipe! So easy, delicious, and I love the texture. I added a cup of chocolate chips. The only thing I would do different would be to use half the amount of salt next time. Thanks for sharing this keeper recipe.

name: zesty oven baked fries
review: Great recipe, yummy fries!  I did cut the heat back to 425F due to other dishes I was cooking at the same time.  Everyone loved them. Thanks for the recipe!

name: kelly s crock pot  smoked  beef roast or brisket
review: Kelly, if I were ever to meet you in person I would hug you for this recipe. IT IS AMAZING!

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: This is so easy and sooooo good.  I looked for the golden mushroom soup but couldn't find it so just used the regular as the recipe stated and it was perfect.  The house smelled so good when my DGSs returned from school that the first thing they asked was "when's dinner" that's unusual for them.  I cut up potatoes, carrots, celery and onions and put on the bottom, browned the roast before putting in the pot and then let it go - the gravy, veggies and roast were done and ready at one time and tasted great.  This is my go to recipe from now on, so easy even the kids can make it themselves.  I have a photo but an issue with the site won't let me upload so will come back and do that once it's fixed.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: Excellent. I added mushrooms because I had some that needed to be used. I cooked the gnocchi in the chicken broth after sauteing the celery, carrot and onion. After the gnocchi were cooked I added the cornstarch to thicken it...    and added the half and half at the very end.

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: This is an amazing marinade ~ would give it 10 stars if I could.  I've only used this with lamb and it was wonderful.  Can't wait to try it on chicken.  Thanks for posting this.

name: jalapeno popper burgers
review: These burgers are fantastic!  They were so moist. Can't wait to have them again.  Thanks for posting.

name: boeuf bourguignon a la julia child
review: I hesitated to review this at all, as I'm a vegetarian!  But I made this for our supper club last week, following the zillion steps to the "T", and at the end of the day...hmmm.  My husband and our 15 guests enjoyed it, ate it up, and it was obviously good, but...husband said that my "usual" recipe (far shorter to make) is actually much better.  ALL DAY to make what amounts to beef stew?  Sorry, Julia; love you, but...

name: pizza dough and sauce
review: Yummy. Followed recipe almost but added lots of toppings (salami, peppers, onions, and mushrooms).  Used 1/2 whole wheat.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: This was definitely a winner. I didn't get to add the red wine; it was still delicious without but I'm sure it would be even more tasty with it! It was super easy to put together and makes for a perfect comfort meal. Thank you!

name: mean guy s general tso s chicken
review: We did enjoy this chicken very much and we had no problem eating up the leftovers and it is at the top of my list, but it's not quite like what Chinese restaurants make.  This is not a criticism of the submitter, as I've been trying for years to make that "perfect restaurant clone" and have turned out unsuccessful.  What is that secret ingredient(s)??  Anybody want to give it up, I'll take it..............

name: artichoke and chicken bake
review: 10 Stars!!!!!  It earned an extra 5 for ease of preparation!!  The only modification I made was I added about 1/3 a cup of diced onion.  Totally amazing, thanks sooooo much Yooper!

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: This was a very easy, quick and delicious dinner!  I would definitely make it again with a few changes.  More veggies, it was a bit boring with no veggies, although I did add carrots and onion.  I would also add more rice. I did up the lentils to 1 full cup instead of 3/4 after reading reviews of it being soupy, which is was a bit soupy even after adding more lentils.  I think more rice will also help.  It was enjoyed by everyone in my family though!  Thanks for this fast and inexpensive recipe!!

name: one minute flax muffin   low carb
review: Very tasty for a healthy breakfast. I used brown sugar and put apple butter on it. Need to eat it while it is warm. Use Pam on coffee mug and clean up is easy.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Other than the special sauce being a little too thin, this is a wonderful recipe! Will make it again. Thank you for posting!

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: I halved the recipe and this turned out delicious!  I made exactly as posted, and found I didn't need any salt, just added a bit of pepper.  I really enjoyed this soup, and its so easy to make I'm sure I'll do this often during the cool weather (I never really have "cold" weather). Thanks so much for sharing...l don't know how I've missed this gem as long as I've been on the website.  Thanks for offering on PRMR.

name: kittencal s scalloped potato and ground beef casserole
review: Comfort food at its finest. I sliced the potatoes very thin and left the skins on for nutrition. I thought there was a bit too much cheese, so I will leave out the middle layer next time and only use 1 cup on top.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: This review is for the spice blend only.  I've never used a recipe to make chili before and simply used my mom's method, adding "a little of this and a little of that."  Getting tired of the hit and miss nature of that, I tried this spice blend.  I'm happy to say I've used it 3 times now with wonderful, consistent (hurray!) results.  Never again will I be forced throw out a pot of chili due to having a horrible seasoning miss.

name: all purpose stir fry sauce  brown garlic sauce
review: I used 1/2 the soy sauce and substituted it with water but it was still very salty.  Good flavor but seemed to be missing something.

name: quick soft breadsticks
review: Coming home on this rainy day, I knew it would be a soup and homemade bread sort of night.  However, I didn't have the 5 hours it takes to make my favorite bread recipe. These were a great substitute. I took one star off, not for taste or texture, but because if I didn't have bread baking experience, the directions probably would not have been enough.  I proofed the yeast in the water and sugar until foamy.  I then added the oil (evoo), flour and salt mixture.  I kneaded it the Kitchen Aid for about 5 minutes.  The taste and texture were wonderful and I will definitely be making these again.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Oh my, these were wonderful!  I thought the sauce would taste like any teriyaki sauce but it was so much more...kind of sweet and savory at the same time.  Seriously, you will lick your plate clean!  Definitely make extra sauce so you can put it on rice.

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: It's a keeper!  I got my squash from a local farmer's market - not sure how big it was - it took an hour to cook to soft.  I took the advice of others and sauteed a small onion and a half of a yellow bell pepper (both chopped) and then used Mexican flavored tomatoes instead of the recommended Rotel tomatoes/chilis (Mexican flavor has jalapenos and is a little spicier but a lot more flavorful).  First bite was OK, then took a second bite with a little salsa, then a third with a little salsa and a little sour cream and WOW was it delish!  Hubby went back for seconds!  We had it as a main dish but it would be great as a side to chicken too.  And then before we put it in the fridge and it was luke warm we each took one last bite and both immediately came to the conclusion that it is BEST that way (flavors just popped).  Will make it again.

name: tsr version of starbucks pumpkin scones by todd wilbur
review: I doubled the spices as suggested by Chef Nadindin. Followed many of her suggestions as well. Very tender and moist. Prepped from beginning to end in a food processor. A great treat with a hot cop of coffee or tea! Thanks for posting Rachel-Snachel!

name: tsr version of chili s chicken enchilada soup by todd wilbur
review: Love this soup.  Made half a recipe and was perfect for the two of us.  DH had three helpings.  Made fried corn tortilla strips to top it.

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: This was very good.  I went easy with the Cajun spice, but in the end it was not spicy at all, so next time I will use more. I also used 1 cup of cream, but could have used more as there was no sauce after adding the pasta.

name: slow cook down home pork chops and gravy
review: Wow.. I'm not much for crock pot recipes...   but this turned out great.  My mom really liked it, too. I added thinly sliced onions and put a couple of chunks of carrot and celery into the crock. I can already think of using this same concept with the broth and seasoned flour mixture and doing chicken, too. ... with a little poultry seasoning.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: I made this with 6 rabbit legs (so, no skin). I discovered there wasn't enough soy sauce when I was already into it, so used the diluted Worcestershire sauce substitution. The sauce was really thin so at 45 minutes, I took most of it out and boiled it to reduce it. After an hour at 350, I put the thickened sauce on, then put it under the broiler for a few minutes to caramelize the rest.  The rabbit was tender and the sauce was tasty.

name: peanut butter no bake cookies
review: Absolutely delicious !!! These were so easy to make and I had everything on had. I just love not having to go to the store. My family loves these cookies. Thank you for the recipe.

name: soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: These will definitely be made again, TNT cookies. I was worried the dough would be too dry but it mixed up and was just very firm. My daughter said these are like the dough that you can buy in tubs, so I think this would make a great gift for the holidays. The only other recipe I have used that came out this soft had pudding mix in it, which I think defeats the purpose of making them from scratch.

name: quick spanish rice
review: Yum! I used diced tomatoes with mild chiles and fresh oregano from the garden. Thanks!

name: sue b s chocolate cake
review: Kaitie-Pie made this cake for my 32nd birthday. and boyyyy was it yummy! she got the baking powder/ baking soda mixed up and it still turned out great! :)

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: The Best brussels sprouts ever.  I sliced each sprout in half to increase the crispy edginess and just used plenty of salt and pepper.  It's amazing that my husband loved them...and he wouldn't even LOOK at a sprout in the past.  These are so good that I plan on adding brussels sprouts to my garden next year.  Thank you so much for posting this recipe Sharon :)

name: denny s style french toast
review: We really enjoyed this recipe! It took me a while to get the heat right on the pan and I think the slices where the pan was hotter came out better. The slices I cooked in more butter also came out tasting better (of course!) Thanks for a lovely recipe!

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: This is a simply delicious recipe...so simple to make and amazingly tasty. I used Panko (didn't feel like making breadcrumbs) and my homemade ranch dressing. I baked the chicken thighs on a rack, on a foil lined cookie sheet, to drain any grease. I think you could use this light and crispy breading on anything, just by changing the herb and can't wait to start experimenting. This is a must try recipe that I'll be using often. What a find! Thank you for posting KeeWee.

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: Very good even without the black beans (thought I had some but didn't).  Normally I am the only one eating Spaghetti Squash but this time the whole family did!

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: This is wonderful. I used my tagine because I love it so much and could not have been more pleased with the results. It's like sitting to table on a rooftop terrace in Marakesh. The flavors meld exquisitely and offer pure satisfaction. Thank you Karen, I still miss you.

name: ww 5 can soup
review: Great soup that tastes perfect and good enough for company.  I tweaked it by skipping on the mixed veggies and adding a can of Progresso Vegetarian Vegetable soup instead (used Progresso Minestrone for the other) - that adds a little bit of pasta and more veggies without all the salt from the can of mixed veggies.  Love that it comes together so simply and fills up my family easily.  Will fall back on this recipe many times through the colder months.

name: basic sourdough bread
review: This is a 10 STAR recipe right here!  Followed the directions exactly, baking the bread for 40 minutes at the 350 degree stage. Next time I will only go with 30 to 35 minutes, for a little softer bottom crust.  Now for the taste-It was the best bread I have ever tasted, and I cannot believe that lil old me made it!  Thanks for the recipe, Donna.

name: ant  kelly s london broil marinade
review: delicious! we typically grill it over high heat for 6 min per side...perfect medium rare.

name: chicken with fettuccine alfredo
review: Good and quick to fix. Not a traditional Alfredo, but a nice creamy garlic sauce. Next time I'll increase the pasta and sauce since everyone wanted more. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: strawberry julius
review: Refreshing!  Delicious!  Easy!  Healthy!   What more could you want?!!  I used 4 cups of fresh strawberries and didn't bother slicing them.  I just cut the green tops off and threw them in my vitamix.  Although I quadrupled the strawberries, I only doubled all the other measurements.  I was afraid of 1) overflowing the vitamix, and 2) it being too liquidy.  I am so glad I made that call.  Even with only doubling the other ingredients it was still very thin.  I thought it needed to be colder so I added 1 1/2 - 2 c of ice and blended that up.  My whole family enjoyed this for dessert.  Next time I think I will add a little bit of fresh lemon juice or orange juice to enhance the strawberry flavor.

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: Very easy & quick recipe.  I didn't have shortening so I used 1 c. butter and it was perfect.  Will definiatley use this again!!

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: With so many reviews, there isn't much more to say, except thank you for sharing this recipe!!!!

name: monastery lentils
review: This was very good!  I used a mix a chicken and beef stock.  I did find it a bit too soupy at the end so I scooped a bit of liquid off the top.  A nice hearty one pot meal!

name: best low carb bread  bread machine
review: Wonderful! I didn't notice any overpowering soy flavor like with other baked things I've made but I'll still try this with coconut flour to get another flavor. Used the machine for dough then finished in the oven. Looked like regular bread but deceptively squishy to handle. I got 12 satisfying sized slices from this. Will definitely make this frequently. My only recipe change was to add a quarter teaspoon of salt. Thanks for sharing.

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: This soup has potential but I found the broth rather bland so I doubled the dried spices, added garlic powder and some parmesan rinds, 1 C cabbage, 1 small zucchini. I  used canned Northern white beans and boiled the pasta separately, as I always do.  The flavors cam together nicely after my tweaks. Because I added several additional ingredients to the soup, I don't feel it is fair to rate as written. Thanks for posting.

name: pizza dough for thin crust pizza
review: This dough made a great thin-crust pizza!  I did prebake the crust for a little less than 10 minutes and brushed the top with a little olive oil first.  Thin and crispy, this made a fantastic pizza - thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Loved this! Made exactly as directed, and the cutlets were enjoyed by all. Easy, healthy and yummy.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Wish it looked prettier but the taste makes up for the awful presentation!  Makes a wonderful dinner and even better as a chip dip.  You wont be sorry you tried this.  **I've now made this at least 100 times and I always add a package of spicy taco seasoning and a large dollop of Bufalo Chipotle sauce along with the salsa.  I've even got over the weird pinky look!

name: pepsi pork roast
review: Very good. The roast came out so tender. Due to some food intolerances, I wasn't able to eat the gravy, but my husband loved it. I was surprised that the meat actually had that distinctive Pepsi flavor. To make this gluten-free, I used Pacific Cream of Mushroom Soup and Simply Organic Onion Dip Mix.

name: easy cole slaw
review: Just what I was looking for, normal cole slaw.  I added a little grated onion too.

name: chicago italian beef
review: Great sandwiches!  I used sub rolls for mine and also had a rump roast about 2 1/2 lbs. so I used 1 can of consommé although I did use the entire pkg. of Italian dressing mix.  I was nervous about the pepperoncini so I only used about a quarter of a jar but it was no problem at all, not too spicy.  I subbed some jarred roasted red peppers for the giardianella.  Thanks for posting.  Made for Cooking Tag mania 2013.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Nice easy mac & cheese - so much better than the boxed stuff!  Thanks for posting.  Will definitely make this again.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Just like Olive Garden!

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: We all liked this. Didn't have peas so I put in a can of green beans and little pastas. No other added salt exept the lipton soup and soy sauce. Good for a cold evening. Well as cold as it can get in San Diego.

name: basic machine french bread
review: They say that bread making is a science...   and I can tell you now that just THAT little bit of flour or salt... or NO oil.. makes a huge difference. I've been experimenting for a while now with different bread recipes and you'd think that just a 1/4 cup of this or a 1/4 tsp. of that wouldn't change it much... well... let me tell you..   it is a difference of great proportions in taste. This is THE recipe ........  I made 3 different recipes today (for the football playoff game) (each has been reviewed here previously) and hands down.. this is the winner. I didn't bake this in the machine.. I split it into two long loaves and baked at 400° for about 25 minutes (I sprayed the oven with a spritz of water when I put them in).. Thanks for a taste that we've been searching for. I think I need to bake it a bit longer for a crispier crust. YUM.. :-)<br/>UPDATE: 11/06/13 This is still a terrific recipe. I've replace one cup of whole wheat flour for a cup of white bread flour and added a little Vital Wheat Gluten. I made two baguettes and they turned out beautifully.

name: cheesy ham and potato soup
review: Great soup.  Made half a recipe for the two of us but used kielbasa instead of ham.  Turned out great with a slice of creamy rye bread.

name: crazy crust pizza
review: Great recipe, especially for someone like me who lives alone.  I make 1/2 of the recipe and bake it in a cornmeal sprinkled pie plate.  And as far as toppings, anything goes.  I've made completely without any kind of meat as well as with the beef and/or pepperoni.  I especially love it with only greens, mushrooms, and grape tomatoes.  I usually eat 1/2 of it, wrap the rest in plastic wrap and heat it the next day for lunch.       <br/><br/>I really like this recipe.  It satisfies my pizza cravings without adding so many calories.

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: This was REALLY easy to make. I only had a can of cheddar broccoli soup, so I used that. The chicken was good, but the sauce was even better. We served with noodles.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: This recipe needs a review!  I have nothing to add, but admiration at how good these rolls turned out.  Some reviewers have stated there needs to be 2 rising times, I didn't do an extra rise.  I baked my cinnamon rolls for 12 minutes.  Next time I make these I will slightly warm up the icing so it will spread easier.  Thanks so much for sharing this recipe, Lightly Toasted.

name: best baked potato
review: These were good and easy to make. I used olive oil and placed the potatoes on a cookie sheet. My potatoes were huge so they took an hour and a half to cook. We all enjoyed these.

name: cheddar bar b q chicken breasts
review: This is a must try.  It was simply delicious.  So quick and easy too.  Thanks for posting such a lovely recipe.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: This was so easy and so delicious.  I loved that it used simple items I had in my pantry but seemed like such an exotic dish.  I'll be doing this one again!  Thanks.

name: whatever floats your boat  brownies
review: Very good recipe! My guests loved them. I used walnuts and chocolate chips (that's what happened to float my boat today). :-)    I was surprised to see no baking soda or baking powder in the recipe... but continued on with great success. This will be my 'go to' brownie recipe from now on. I'll be sure to line the pan next time because I ruined the first two brownies trying to get them out of the pan. They were gobbled up so quickly that I didn't get a chance to take a picture.<br/>UPDATE 11/9/2013: Still no picture..   but added 1/2 cup of Skor pieces and they were devoured. I lined the pan with crosswise strips of parchment paper so when they were cool they lifted easily out of the pan and cut nicely.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: Thank you for my new FAVORITE cauliflower recipe! I'd give more than 5 stars if I could. Enough said!

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: I like pumpkin pancakes, but my husband LOVES them.  These have the perfect amount of spice and pumpkin.

name: beth s melt in your mouth barbecue ribs  oven
review: I can not play with this absolutely awesome!  I don't have to watch them so closely. Fabulous ribs, and clean up is so easy to do! Thank You Grpa

name: awesome baked ham
review: this was not bad.......but not as good as the recipe I usually use.  Somehow the mustard was the problem............in fact, the family had a few "problems" after eating it.  I just hate to give a bad review, and evidently many people do like it, so I will just say it is not for us.  Please know this is just a matter of taste and not a fault of a good recipe.   <br/>Donna

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: This was a nice Autumn recipe. I enjoyed the sweetness and the kids liked it. Husband despises all things squash, but I managed to get a few bites down him. Only complaint was that the squash lost a bit of texture and was a might mushier than I expected... next time I would cut down on the butter to see if that helped.

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Excellent. The sauce is not quite exactly like PF Chang's, but it is still a delicious dish and definitely repeat worthy. I did not deep fry the meat, halved the soy/water (it was still plenty) and used only 2 tablespoons of the brown sugar (so it would not be sweet for us). Next time I would also increase the aromatics, maybe add more flavors to increase the complexity of the sauce, and add the cornstarch to the sauce instead of the meat, to avoid the mess that created. I think this would work equally well to halve the meat and add veggies to it too. A thoroughly enjoyable meal!

name: mexican enchilada sauce
review: This has got to be the BEST sauce I've ever had, it is sure going into my BEST of 2013 Book.  Was making recipe 121147 and didn't have any canned so choose this one to try.  You are so right about the cocoa being a much needed for this recipe.  The only thing I did differant was cut it in half as it was just DH and me but should have made the full amount to have on hand.  Next time I'll also try the cumin but don't know how it could be any better.  DH said "make sure you tell everyone how great it is" that's some compliment as he never says much.  I also liked that it was pretty fast, without a long simmer time.  The photo is not the prettiest but it sure tasted great

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: Wonderfully fluffy and light

name: my no roll pie crust
review: This is my best attempt at pie crust.  I've always overworked them in the past...no more, this is a great recipe.  I mixed it until ingredients are just barely incorporated, then press into pie dish.  I also made another one for the top and refrigerate about an hour before rolling out.  However, very difficult to do the top as the mixture is so tender and falls apart easily.  Going to roll out and then cut into small leaves to just scatter over the top of my pie this time.  Thank you for a great pie crust.

name: crazy crust pizza
review: I loved the ease and speed this pizza was to prepare.  <br/>The grandkids liked it, and that's what matters.<br/>The cup and a half of sauce may have been the cause of it being soggy in the middle.  <br/>I'll see next time if it turns out less soggy using less sauce.  I made it with no toppings,<br/>just sauce and cheese.  The biggest thing was,  I did not have to spend big $ to feed<br/>the grandkids.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: Delicious, simple, elegant, and lo-cal too?!!!  Awesome recipe.  Made just as written and very happy with the results.  (Had to bake mine a wee bit longer because they were so thick.)  Loved that it didn't demand my attention while I prepared other things and that it only called for items I already had in my pantry. Thanks!

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: Thank you for sharing this simple, quick and delicious recipe. I made my own ranch and it was very thick and I found that I should have doubled both the crumb mixture and the dressing. I used potato chips for the crumbs and my own blend of herbs for the seasoning (oregano, basil and garlic). The leftover chicken reheats well and makes an amazing sandwich.

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: First off...I LOVE tuna and noodles.  I always have.  I always will.  Don't ask me why, it's just one of life's great mysteries.  This is the best version I have ever had!  I never, never, ever would have thought of adding mayo.  *WOW* does it make a difference!  We did add peas because, well...because peas must be included.  (At least we think so.)  Thanks for the recipe!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Very good! I made this with out the meat. Hubby brought home a #10 can of tomato sauce, so I used that for all the tomato products and doubled everything. I added 3 or 4 palmfuls of sugar to help with the bite of the canned tomato. After the sauce cooked, I added a few labels to meat I cooked separately to make lasagna. Yummy! To that 2 pounds of browned ground meat I added a small palmful of fennel seed, 4 cloves minced garlic, two soup spoonfuls of prepared pesto and 2 palmfulls of Italian seasoning.<br/>Everyone loved the sauce!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: I used a heavy pound of beef (maybe 1.25?), 1/3 c half and half, sautéed my onion in oil, added a 2 green onions that I had on hand, and used a crushed VERY dry piece of whole wheat bread. I mixed the sauce with 3.5 T brown sugar in it 2 hrs early, then just used half of it...the other half is in the freezer for next time. Loved it!!!<br/>***remove the meatloaf from the pan as soon as you take it out of the oven, otherwise it will suck up all of the fat and juices from the pan, making it very soggy.

name: drunken garlic crock pot roast
review: Awesome!  Super easy!  I used a chunk of venison and went light on the brown sugar for personal preference.  I popped this amazing concoction in the crock pot for 8 hrs on low.  The gravy was super good over mashed potato's~~ Thanks Sue Lau!!!

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: I love these!  The topping completes them so they give what I always look for in my muffins--lots of flavor with some crunchiness.

name: bev s macaroni and cheese
review: This is where you stop for that yummy mac and cheese you've been dying to have.  I doubled the recipe and had leftovers (2 adults and 2 kids 7 and 8).

name: melt in your mouth chicken breasts
review: Delicious, and easy.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: Perfect for a quick and delicious meal, I also add fat free half and half toward end and I use an Italian Herb grinder to add a little extra. I am so happy I discovered this recipe.

name: the ultimate greek salad
review: GREAT salad! I LOVED the dressing... but will reduce the oil next time (we like ours very acidic). Also, will sub out the kalamata olives for regular black olives, both for price and preference.

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: I loved how easy this was to make!  I used 2 tsp of jarred jalapeno peppers and garnished with toasted sesame seeds and chopped scallions. My kids want me to try it with boneless breasts next time. Thanks for posting this. I had wanted to try it for some time now!

name: thick and creamy new england clam chowder
review: Absolutely LOVE! I wish I could give this recipe more than 5 stars! Except for using 5 slices of bacon, I made the chowder exactly based on the recipe. It turned out PERFECT according to my DH who's from Boston. I see this one become a regular on our dining table! :)

name: cinnamon swirl quick bread
review: This bread was just OK for me, I probably would not make it again. It did not have much flavor.

name: banana oatmeal bread
review: I really enjoyed the chewiness of this bread and it was so quick and easy. next time i think i will add more banana. thanks for sharing

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: These are really good!  With that said, the special sauce is not quite the same as what you get at Changs but it is still really, really good.  Just makes sure you chop everything very fine.  Yum!

name: slow cooker cheesy chicken
review: Great recipe! Love how easy it is and how delicious it tastes. I threw a bag of frozen mixed veggies in my crock pot together with the butterflied chicken breasts. Cooked on low for 8 hours and served over pasta. Chicken was fork tender when it's done and the sauce absolutely hit the spot!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: Wonderful sauce! This made a lot of spaghetti sauce for 1 person so I canned a lot of it. I will add the mushrooms and Parmesan cheese when I use it.  Made for Zaar Chef Alphabet Soup.

name: stove top tamale pie
review: This was really GOOD!  I cook hamburger ahead of time so this came together really quick.  We will have this often, thank you!

name: p  f  chang s mongolian beef by todd wilbur
review: Loved this! I pretty much followed the recipe, except I cut the sugar in half and used gluten-free tamari instead of soy sauce. Even with those changes it was wonderful. Served over rice. Will definitely be making this again!

name: general tso s chicken  tso chung gai
review: Fabulous recipe, far better than take out chinese!!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: This is probably the best tasting meatloaf I've ever had! I did have a little trouble with the texture, however, but it was probably my own fault. I found it to be a bit crumbly, but I'm suspecting it is because I didn't blend the mixture well enough and because I used gluten-free (gf) bread. I would probably recommend using gf bread crumbs instead of bread to make this gf. I used regular white vinegar instead of apple cider and green onions due to some food intolerances.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Wonderful, wonderful, wonderful!  I made this to top my son's birthday cake recipe#38966 .  I had to use regular whole milk as I had no half-and-half and I only used 1/3 cup of chocolate (forgetting to sift that).  Even with the changes it was far superior to any store bought frosting.  My son told me that it tastes like fudge, and I think so too.  A go to recipe for me when I need chocolate icing.  Thanks for the recipe Kittencal!

name: quick yellow cake
review: Made this for my son's birthday today. Quite the quick and easy recipe.  And has a good flavor.  I don't think the cake rose as much as a cake mix would have, and it was dry and lacked structure.  I tried to follow the recipe exactly, but may have done something wrong, or perhaps my baking powder was limp.  I did bake the cake for 35 minutes, next time I will only let it go 30 minutes, see if that helps the dryness.  I topped the cake with recipe#89207 .  All in all, I loved the ease and taste, and will make again.  Thanks for sharing MizzNezz

name: best albondigas soup
review: This is delicious soup. I love the subtle kick of heat the chorizo added to the meatballs.  I baked the fro about 20 minutes to avoid adding fat to the soup. Worked out beautifully. My fabulous husband could not stop complimenting the soup. It's a winner. Just as good on day 2! Thanks for sharing your family recipe RuizA.

name: hello dollies
review: Oh my gosh this is so good!! I did the 6 T. of butter and about 1 1/4 c. graham cracker crumbs in a 9x13" pan. Added rest of ingredients in this order: coconut, nuts (1/2 pecans; 1/2 walnuts), then chocolate chips. Very rich!!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I thought I had reviewed this a long time ago!?! I make this recipe several times a year.  Its great! Moist, tasty and freezes well! My husband loves using these sandwiches for lunch.  I tried it one time with beer instead of ginger ale, and that was great too, but usually I use ginger ale.

name: chicken pesto
review: Sorry, but we just did not like this.  Like some others said the chicken was moist but the flavor was bland and the breadcrumbs that super soggy. We will not make this again.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: Fantastic chili!  I added half a large green pepper, a couple stalks of celery, and three serrano chilies, seeds and membranes in.  I try to sneak in veggies wherever possible.  ;o)  All four guys loved it, and the picky one (13 yr old) even had two bowls!!  This is my go-to chili from now on!  Thanks so much, Debbie, for this fantastic recipe!  Only change next time is to double the recipe!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: We enjoyed this... in fact, it tastes just like the BBQ pork in the BBQ Pork Fried Rice we order as Chinese take-out (except it isn't as dry)! It was super easy to throw together and it smelled wonderful baking. I made as directed, except I used BBQ sauce instead of ketchup in the sauce. It was a little bit salty, so I would use a low-sodium soy sauce next time.

name: the best chili you will ever taste
review: I didn't use the exact amount of ingredients to cook the chili according to this recipe. I cut everything in half and skipped dark beer. Didn't feel like putting too much sugar in, so only added 1 tablespoon brown sugar. Instead of using dried cilantro, fresh cilantro was sprinkled over the chili when it's done. Chili sauce was substituted with homemade chili oil. It turned out really good! Thanks for posting!

name: cauliflower cheddar soup
review: I just bought an immersion blender and this is the first recipe I tried it out on. I added some Beau Monde Seasoning, a little garlic powder (on top of the 3 garlic cloves) and freshly cracked black pepper besides the salt and ground mustard. It has wonderful flavors and I bet it will even taste better tomorrow! Thanks for posting!

name: croutons
review: Really easy and good. Next time I'll use half butter and half olive oil. I like the taste a little better. Thanks for posting the recipe.

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Made mine as garlic toast using a loaf of Italian bread from the bakery.  Garlic butter spread is delicious!

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: I have it all in now- added everything after the beef browned.  I added a packet of onion soup because I only had 2 smallish onions and I used 3 cups of broth and 1 cup of red wine. I added the additional red pepper flakes, 2 bay leaves and rosemary.  For potatoes I used red potatoes. I didn't add celery cause I didn't have any. I cut the veggies into chunks instead of dicing. Smells great simmering on the stove! Yum!

name: easy cole slaw
review: Very nice.  Added about a tbsp of horseradish as others had recommended and made with a mix of cabbage and carrots..

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Lovely way to do an old favourite,  and so easy :)    Thank you Sharon, made and enjoyed for PRMR tag game

name: world s best cinnamon raisin bread  not bread machine
review: Wow!!  This was SO good!  Just what I was craving.  Made pretty much as written and really glad you posted the recipe.  Thanks!

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: Very tasty and really easy to make! Made it without any changes. Just like everyone said, it's a little bland. Would probably try to add more ingredients next time. This is a great potato soup base though!

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
