I also had no mustard powder but added a little onion soup mix. I think it's fairly versatile if you go with good flavors. I ended up taking out the pork chops and adding a bit more broth to thin it out and to make there be more of such an amazing thing. I will make this again and again!

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: Delicious!  I get a craving for curry once in awhile and this fit the bill!  The only change I made was to use regular raisins instead of the golden because that's what I had and I chopped them up really fine so my family wouldn't know they were in there.  I definitely think you need the taste of the raisins in it, they add so much.  I made naan bread to go with this.

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: This was a great recipe for key lime pie and so easy!  I made a graham cracker crust and added some lime zest.  I also added meringue to the top because you have to have meringue!

name: lisa s swirled chocolate chip cookies
review: Good cookies! I made exactly as directed, except with only 2 cups chocolate chips. I did discover that at 350, the cookies needed to be taken out of the oven while just beginning to brown at the edges- they the are perfect when cooled. At 325, they spread out much more and I got a thinner cookie. Perfect choc. chip recipe, and makes a good amount of large cookies. I got maybe 6 dozen 4inch cookies?

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: I liked the method--I hate having to remember the yeast last.  But as for the flavor...it was nothing special to me.  Not even as toast.

name: chili s salsa
review: Absolutely love! This salsa recipe is so easy and delicious! I did make a few minor changes though. I used one fresh japanero pepper with the seeds in. Didn't have garlic salt, so instead, I added 1/2 tsp sea salt and 1/4 tsp garlic powder. I think 1-2 cloves fresh garlic will do just fine. After all, great recipe! Will make it again for sure!

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Amazing recipe! I used gluten-free tamari sauce instead of the soy sauce and it came out sooo tasty! I will definitely make these again. Next time I will try cooking them on the stove top instead of the oven, like so many other reviewers recommend. I served mine with a millet pilaf and salads.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: I'm so proud to be adding the 100th review to this recipe!  It was a huge success, although I cooked this on the stovetop, rather than in the slow cooker.  I used all the ingredients as directed, except I had to add some butter to saute the vegetables in, before adding the chicken.  This smelled absolutely wonderful while it was cooking.  I saw some complaints about the color, but the roasted garlic cream of mushroom soup is a darker color (and not that pasty stuff) so it was appetizing to look at as well.  Thanks for sharing!

name: streamlined chimichangas
review: I'm always looking for quick and simple weeknight dinner ideas using ground beef. This will be made time and time again! So good! Thanks for the recipe.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: We thought the recipe was good but there were a few problems.  The chops turned out dry and the gravy was really thin so I thickened that up with a slurry of cornstarch. The total cook time listed is way off.  If you cook for the full time listed in the recipe, it should be closer to one hour 30 minutes (add another 10 minutes for prep) so I don't know where the 2 1/2 hrs comes from which is listed at the top of the recipe. All in all though, the flavour is good so by reducing the cooking time and thickening the gravy, I would probably try this again. Thank you for posting!

name: chicken pesto
review: I really appreciate how simple this was to put together... in the summer I'll even make my own pesto which will make it even better! Thanks for the recipe!

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: SAVE THIS IMMEDIATELY!!!! Tortilla soup is hit or miss with me!  I needed a soup that was not in the rotation so I picked this because of the reviews and comment by the chef!  This is the BEST Chicken Tortilla Soup I have ever eaten!!! Only change I made was to reduce the "heat" of the soup to my kids liking.

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: The first bite... we we not happy.....    second bite...   well. yes.   I can eat this...   third bite..   yes.. we like it.  It's a good concept....  it needs veggies...    and some other flavor.....    it was a little too 'processed' if that's a flavor.....   I know 'processed' is not a flavor..  but some of you will know what I mean.

name: strawberry cheesecake trifle
review: I wish I could give this recipe ten stars!!!! Absolutely loved it!! I completely skipped the sugar and mixed the cheese mixture with some leftover Jello cakes. So so so good!!! Will definitely make this again very soon!! Thanks a zillion for posting this fantastic recipe!!

name: fresh strawberry cake
review: Very good cake which we enjoyed. Instead of the round cake pans we used a heart shaped pan (fairly large) and cooked the cake for 45 minutes. Delish!

name: company pork roast
review: I am not going to rate this as I made some significant changes  based on what I had on hand & timing. I left out both the vinegar & the mustard powder, then went in an Asian direction, adding some white wine, a little sesame oil & ground ginger. Marinated everything in a zip top bag for several hours. I placed everything in the slow cooker with some sliced onion & carrot sticks. The end result was wonderfully moist & flavorful. Served with steamed jasmine rice & steamed broccoli crowns. My family loved every bite!

name: brown rice and lentil casserole
review: I purchased the same book in the late 80's and had every intention to make this very recipe.   Funny how there's so many things I want to cook, but never get around to as time roller blades by.  Anyway, better late than never, plus Brown Rice & Lentil Casserole = Eatable Happiness.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: Great soup! I made this a while back, when it was very cold and we had a foot of snow on the ground. I started it in the crock-pot (on high) early in the morning so hubby and I could have it for lunch that day. I actually poached a couple boneless / skinless chicken breasts the night before I made this, so it came together quickly. I used the Campbells Cream of Mushroom with Garlic (that's the only cream of mush soup for me). This was the first time I've every put cream of any sort into homemade chicken noodle soup, and it will NOT be the last. It made it so much more rich and filing than plain broth. Oh, and the addition of the frozen peas (which I absolutely L-O-V-E) is a terrific idea. Thanks so much for posting. (Made for PRMR)

name: white almond sour cream wedding cake
review: I cut the recipe in half.  One half recipe made 32 mini cupcakes, a 10" x 15" pan and about 9 regular size cupcakes.  I thought the cake by itself was not very flavorful. But once I added a nice cream cheese frosting, the flavors all came together.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: I made this to frost some lamb cakes for Easter.  Something is very wrong with this recipe.  I didn't print it, I wrote it down and triple checked what I wrote down.  One third cup of half and half is way too much!  I must have added close to 2 cups of powdered sugar before it was icing consistency.  Maybe this should have been 1-3 tablespoons of half and half.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Quick and easy.

name: mexican stuffed shells  oamc
review: This was very good but took a lot of chili powder to give the tomato sauce any flavor. I might try cutting back on the tomato sauce and using enchilada sauce next time.

name: lemon baked cod
review: Note: Food.com is not a WW affiliate and is not allowed to calculate points. Use the tools WW provides, or go to their online calculator.

name: old fashioned banana cream pie
review: Great pie! Very tasty and easy. I made this for Easter and it was a hit.

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: Made this for my son's b'day.  It was great!  Used a different icing recipe 222188 but this cake was great!

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: Oh wow! This was delicious! I used it on my Easter bunny cake this year. So delicious! I used whole milk and only used 1/4 tsp of almond extract. Was the perfect amount to cover the cake with just a little leftover. Will use this again!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: I am a pot pie lovin' lady and I make them frequently.  That being said this ranks up in the very top of all of the pot pie recipes I've made since I've been cooking.  This recipe was very easy and tasted just great.  It was made especially easy because I didn't have to prepare my own crust this time.  I'm sure this will be in the rotation at our house frequently.  The only thing that I changed was that I used 9-inch pie pans instead of the 9x13-inch casserole dish because that is always how I make pot pies.  Thank you for such a winner breezermom!  Made for PAC Spring 2014.

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Terrific!  Helped make a great cake (recipe 26370) for my son's birthday.

name: ranch chicken thighs
review: Great!  Easy and delicious.  I needed about double the breading for 8 thighs but otherwise the recipe was perfect.  Thanks so much KeyWee....

name: pizza dough and sauce
review: Mmmmmm...5 stars for both the sauce and the crust! I used 1 cup WW flour and 3 cups of white flour. My DH was able to get the crust real thin and it held up to the toppings without being limp or soggy. He cooked it on the grill and it only took about 10 mins. The sauce was very flavorful and thick. I used about a 1/4 t. of garlic powder and red wine and it made the sauce kind of tangy, which we really enjoyed. Thanks for the keeper recipe.

name: microwave lemon garlic broccoli
review: This is good.  Very bright flavour and I like the peppers in it.  The only concern I have is that even tender crisp broccoli doesn't "mix" well with a tiny amount of liquid carrying salt and dried peppers and garlic.  I found it hard to get the broccoli evenly coated.  But maybe that will come with practice.  I will definitely make it again.

name: kittencal s spinach parmesan rice bake
review: This was really good.  DH doesn't care for rice much, but he didn't even complain about it being in this.  He likes spinach and said this was pretty good.  That's  worth 5 stars.

name: awesome baked ham
review: This will now become our go-to recipe for ham!!  It was perfect!!  I wouldn't change a thing!<br/>Thank you for posting!!  <br/>update :)<br/>I added 2 tbls of mustard seeds...fabulous!!

name: quick and easy pizza dough
review: Delivers as promised. I used it for a prosciutto and arugula pizza. :)

name: the best apple pie muffins ever
review: I left off the topping entirely. I shredded the apple, added 1/3 c. Quick cooking oatmeal

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: I made this for St. Patty's Day and we enjoyed this very much.  I usually make a corned beef, but your description had me thinking, so I went with your recipe instead.  Big hit.  My family liked it very much.  I used ground beef as I wasn't sure if they would all like the lamb, but I might be more adventurous next time and try the lamb.  Thank you for our holiday meal.  Great choice on my part, thanks to you.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: Very much enjoyed this dish. I used fresh dill, as I don't like the dried very much and shallot instead of the regular onion. Keeper for sure. :)

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: Delicious and easy to make!

name: weight watchers mexican chicken breasts
review: This is not a WW site, so Food.com cannot calculate the points. Please calculate them using the tools you got when you registered, or on the WW site. WW changes its point system every couple of years.

name: bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers
review: Yum! These are so good. My grandson loves to make these for us to snack on. Thanks for sharing this nice keeper. Made for Name That Ingredient Tag.

name: kittencal s spinach   four cheese manicotti  vegetarian
review: Pretty good. I should've added salt. I had skipped it because I thought with all the cheese there would plenty. I also used my own spaghetti sauce with some meat. Had some extra filling, wondering if I could freeze it alone?

name: creamy potato salad
review: I think this might be the best potato salad ever made. I'm so excited to bring it to my fam BBQ tomorrow and show off :) I only used 1/2 tsp of salt, 1tsp celery seeds (mine are kind of old, so I'm not confident about their flavor) and added 4 eggs. Thanks for the forever and ever keeper!!! Update: I make this all the time and it is frequently requested by family. I use 6 slices of bacon, and this past time used 1 tsp of celery salt to replace the celery seed and salt. So delicious thank you!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: I hardly ever rate Chinese food 5 stars because it's always too sweet, or not sweet enough, or just too much of this or that.  Anyway, this definitely was delicious all around and my husband and kids thoroughly enjoyed dinner :)  Thanks!

name: extremely soft white bread   bread machine
review: My BM died so used my KA, turned out very nicely.  I did add 1 T. vital gluten as suggested by another person.

name: alton brown s baked brown rice
review: Easy & comes out perfect.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: These Brussels sprouts were excellent.  I would certainly do these ones again!  Yum!  Kudos on a great find!!!

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: OMG was this delicious!!!  I used frozen bacon, chicken broth and whipping cream that I had in my freezer.  I added 4 garlic cloves...well, because we love garlic!!!  Fast, easy and really good!   Kudos on the find!!!

name: creamy burrito casserole
review: Major!! This was so crazy-delicious, I can't even tell you! We followed some other reviewers advice and added some Pace Picante sauce to the meat and bean mixture, but otherwise followed the recipe exactly! It was so easy too-really inexpensive ingredients coming together really quickly to make this extravaganza of hearty, cheesy, creamy, burrito goodness--mmmm! What a fabulously tasty and simple MONDAY(!) night dinner! Thank you so much!

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: Made just as directed.  I thought it needed a little more salt, but other than that was very good.  We didn't have the problem with the sauce staying on top...ours mixed in nicely with the spaghetti (we did use a 9x13 pan though...I don't know if it would have gone into the spaghetti if is was much deeper).

name: why i joined zaar carrot cake
review: This recipe is a keeper.  It's just a really amazing carrot cake- what more can one say?

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: This is delicious! It tastes just like the Olive Garden's, which my husband and I love! I cut the recipe in half, and it still made enough for dinner and probably two or three days of leftovers. Like most soups, it tastes even better the next day. It was very thick, so I'll probably add some extra beef broth next time, and I think I will use less oregano next time as well. I cooked my pasta on the stove just before serving, and kept it separate from the soup because I do not care for mushy pasta. Thank you so much for sharing, this was super easy and delicious!

name: thick chocolate pudding
review: First, I tried making this on the stove top, but didn't let it cook long enough.  It looked thick in the pot, but didn't set up firm enough.  So I decided to make it as written (what a concept!), letting it go 5.5 minutes after the initial 3, and adding in a couple of tablespoons of semi-sweet chips to up the chocolatiness.  Loved it!  I may cut back to 5 minutes.  So easy in the microwave, and only 1 bowl to clean up.  Thanks!

name: frizzled cabbage
review: This is a wonderful basic recipe that you can add things to. I decided to do what one person did: spread cooked white rice on the bottom of a pan, layered the cooked cabbage over it, layered fried slices of kielbasa and then sprinkle shredded mozzarella all over it and put it in the oven until the cheese melted and started to brown a bit. Made for Chef Alphabet Soup.

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: Great recipe! I halved it and added red onion sauteed in the bacon grease. I think red wine vinegar  works best for our tastes. Added salmon and avocado to make it a dinner salad. Thanks for the keeper!

name: taco bell quesadillas
review: Very good but didn't need the American cheese, would have been good without.  Loved the sauce.

name: most incredible no fail pie crust
review: Very delicious. I made two quiches with this crust. I had trouble rolling it out...   it kept cracking...   so I just pressed it into the dishes. It worked and tastes great. I don't care what it looks like.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: This lasagna was VERY full of taste!  I have had so many first here on zaar/food, and this is another one.  The sauce part of the recipe was the best tasting homemade red sauce I have tried or made.  Smelling the sauce as it cooked was heavenly The recipe is a little fussy, but not difficult at all.  Left overs were better the next day.  Froze the rest for later.  I have defrosted and reheated frozen leftovers and I think the taste suffers not one iota. Better than frozen Stouffers.  Just getting around to reviewing, made this the middle of last month. Thanks for posting this recipe ratherbeswimmin!

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: I prepared this sauce tonight for salmon and chicken.  While it had a good taste, we found that it was just a bit too sweet for us.  I may use the leftover for a marinade only.

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: I have been making these for a couple years now and realized I've never reviewed them. These are a huge hit with my family! DH and 7yo DD request these ALL THE TIME. DD can pretty much eat her weight in lettuce wraps. The only changes I make are to use ground turkey or pork because I'm allergic to chicken, and I use dehydrated onion flakes instead of onion due to sensitive tummies. I also usually add some shredded carrots. The special sauce combines much easier if you just throw it in the blender.  I also double up on the stir fry sauce :)  We eat this at least once a month, which means its a serious winner in our book!

name: carb free cloud bread
review: One of my daughters and I liked them, the other was not lovin it. Used two as a bun for sloppy joes.

name: the  blue mill tavern loosemeat sandwich
review: This was better than I expected, I'm glad I tried it!  I thought it might be bland but not at all.  I did top it with a slice of cheese, had to do it.  Will definitely make again!

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Loved this - can't believe I haven't rated this.  Made this tonight - as written and it was awesome.  Make it!  You'll be happy you did!

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: I made this with my son in mind. We both loved it!  I made it exactly as posted and can imagine adding some other veggies for color, but it was perfect just they way it is.  Thanks for sharing.  Made for Zaar Cookbook Tag game.

name: simple sweet scones
review: Very good! This is a biscuit-y scone, not too dry. I definitely think the extra sugar is a must, and I like to brush the tops with egg white or milk before sprinkling with sugar. This gives a nice sweet crisp top, which gives your scones the edge! I enjoyed adding a mixture of diced dried blueberries, cherries, prunes & craisins.  Hubby doesn't usually like dried fruit in baked goods but he enjoyed this version!

name: roasted garlic mashed potatoes   the best you ve ever had
review: Delicious recipe! I'm sensitive to garlic (but love it), so I cut it back. I used unpeeled red potatoes and added some salt to the water to cook them in.

name: perfect basic white rice
review: I usually use a rice cooker, but wanted to learn to make rice on the stove. This recipe was the perfect place to start! I used jasmine rice, and skipped the butter and salt. Also, note that, to get the requisite amount of steam, I ended up needing to turn the burner to low.

name: strawberry shortcake a la treebeard s
review: This is a great dessert that needs a couple of modifications to make it the best.<br/><br/>I'll say right off the bat that the cooking time or temperature is too high.  I cooked ours 15 minutes then checked it and the shortcake was already overdone... dark/slightly burned on the bottom and just a little too dark on the top.  But I sliced off the very bottom and it was still a great dessert.<br/><br/>This is what I would do to improve it...<br/>1)  Make smaller cakes (I would make about 9 cakes out of the recipe as written).<br/>2)  Make more berry mixture.  I would use about 50% more berries and adjust the recipe accordingly (we ran out of berries... better too much than not enough).<br/>3)  Bake on 390 degrees F, check at 13 minutes and add a little time if necessary.<br/>4) The sugar (both powder and granulated sugar) can easily be cut in half in the whipped cream mixture and it is still PLENTY SWEET!<br/><br/>Great recipe, thanks!

name: southern fried chicken
review: This came out excellent!  I had never made fried chicken before, so was a bit worried. I put the seasonings in with the dredging flour and used Frank's hot sauce. Also, because I double-dipped my chicken, I had just the right amount of flour. Thanks for posting, Sharlene!

name: 1 pan fudge cake
review: This was delicious! I can't believe there is no milk or eggs in it! I wanted something sweet and homemade for dessert last night but didn't want to go to a lot of trouble or make a big mess, and this was perfect! I did not frost mine, just sprinkled some powdered sugar on top when it came out of the oven. It is very moist and yummy. I will make this again for sure, thank you for sharing!

name: basil pesto
review: Made this after pruning back my patio basil plant.  I have not experienced pesto before so I can't compare.  After processing this, it tasted rather raw.  I put it in a bowl and placed clear plastic wrap, expelling all air, on top of bowl and pesto.  I did add some Italian parsley, to make up for a small deficit of available basil.  The nuts were omitted because I had none on hand.  Used bottled lemon juice and added a pinch of salt. Thanks for posting, Bonnie Traynor.

name: classic baked spaghetti
review: Easy to make.  I added some chopped broccoli, zucchini and onion to the boiling water also.  I also added salt, pepper and turmeric.  Liked by all, so that the whole 1-1/2 batch disappeared between 4 people!  I think 1 batch (8 oz noodles) would not be enough for a family of 4.  Only if not real hungry. :)

name: teresa s veal  or chicken piccata
review: Really good recipe. 4 stars because it could be improved by reducing the oil and butter. I sprayed the pan and used only 1 T olive oil. I used chicken breast in this recipe and it worked well. Also mixed some panko with the ap flour. I didn't have a lemon but did have some lemon juice leftover forms lemon off our tree I had zested a few days ago. I added some artichoke hearts which made it a meal. Thanks for sharing this!

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: I had all the ingredients on hand.   I had 2 pans going because they were sort of steaming and I wanted a little browning.  I skipped the parsley.  It was very nice!  Thanks Update- I had a bag of cooked large shrimp. I made al dente pasta and set it aside then added a bit more oil and garlic and followed all but skipped the zest. I added some onion too cause I had it and then I heated the shrimp in the mixture until heated and placed them on the pasta. I added a little cornstarch and water to thicken the sauce and poured it on top. I even took some garlic croutons and crushed them and sprinkled that on top. It was a hit! Thanks

name: amazing chicken tortilla soup
review: I made this almost exactly as written except I used homemade shrimp stock that I had on hand and it was really delicious. Even my husband kept saying how good it was. Thank you for sharing it!!

name: vanilla  buttercream frosting  from sprinkles cupcakes
review: Perfect butter cream icing! It spreads beautifully, would change a thing. Thanks for sharing the keeper recipe.

name: hershey s chocolate cake with frosting
review: 42 minutes in a 9x13. Excellent cake!

name: kittencal s  brown sugar caramel sauce or ice cream topping
review: Oh......yummmmmm!!  Delicious!!!  I used previous suggestions to use real vanilla bean as I had some to use up!  This sauce is fast and easy...made up in 5 minutes!!!  This recipe is not your traditional caramel sauce...you definitely can taste the brown sugar in the sauce.  Thanks Kittencal for sharing!!!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: We really enjoyed this one! I added panko to give an extra crunch to the the chicken.  These came out so juicy and flavorful.  Thanks!!!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: Tried and true x 2!

name: p  f  chang s chicken lettuce wraps by todd wilbur
review: Yummy! These were great! I used ground chicken because I had some on hand, so there was no need to chop up the chicken after cooking it. I used green onions instead of regular onions, and I ended up adding a little extra of the stir fry sauce ingredients. This is much better than my regular lettuce wrap recipe, and I will definitely be making it again. Thank you for sharing!

name: amazing chicken marinade
review: The name says it all; this is AMAZING!  Made as written and marinated b/s chicken breasts for 10 hours and then grilled.  It is the perfect balance of sweet and tang!  DH loves grilled chicken but ooh'd and ahh'd throughout the entire meal.  Going into my Best of 2014 Cookbook.  Made for Name that Ingredient Tag.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: An amazing recipe!! It's hard to find new options for Kielbasa--we used the turkey variety. I used about 2 cups diced potatoes--the recipe calls for a lot more but that seemed like too much for my husband's tastes. I also skipped the green pepper (he doesn't like them) & added some garlic powder into the seasoning mix. I used a low fat Mexican cheese, and my potatoes were cooked in about 15 min--probably since I reduced the amount. I sure liked the one skillet convenience & my husband ate it right up. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: kittencal s moist cheddar garlic oven fried chicken breast
review: These were easy to make, and enjoyed by the family.  Thank you!

name: 24k carrots
review: Yummy way to make carrots!  Thanks!!!

name: eggs with hats on top
review: I made this this morning for the DM's breakfast and she thoroughly enjoyed. I made just the one using wholemeal/wholegrain bread and toasted one side first and then cut the circle out and buttered the untoasted side and put that in the hot frypan and slipped the egg into the hole and then put a lid on the frypan and cooked until the egg was set and the yolk still soft, toasted the other side of the circle and served that for dipping into the yolk.  Thank you Sheri-BDB, made for Name that Ingredient tag game.

name: easy banana muffins
review: Enjoyed this recipe. Really simple to make, delicious results, easy to modify for diet/health/preference. I substituted Splenda for Sugar and Apple Sauce for Butter. I used the optional salt and used about 1/4 cup of semi-sweet chocolate chips. 1-year-old twins LOVED the muffins. A fun treat for a breakfast-on-the-go!

name: carb free cloud bread
review: These came out surprisingly well. I baked them closer to 35 to 40 minutes to get them nice and browned. I was having trouble stirring the cream cheese into the egg yolks, so I used a whisk instead of a spoon to beat the mixture and it worked much better.

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: Very very good! I did exactly what the recipe states, only added more cheese on top right before setting my baking dish in the oven. The flavor was excellent!!! Will be making this again for sure! Thanks for posting!

name: english muffins  bread machine method
review: How fantastic! Muffins skillet fried! Very good they are, too.

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Delicious easy wonderful pancakes.  Made for I recommend.

name: top secret recipes version of kfc coleslaw by todd wilbur
review: Yum!  Halved the recipe and used bagged coleslaw mix with no problems.  Thank you!

name: croutons
review: I don't like store-bought croutons, so I was happy to find this recipe.  And I had hot dog buns leftover to use - this is such a great thing to do with leftover bread.  I used less salt, and added fresh cracked pepper.  Really nice!  Thanks for posting!

name: tsr version of carrabba s bread dipping spice by todd wilbur
review: So happy to find this recipe. This dipping spice was WONDERFUL. I had fresh parsley and garlic available in my kitchen. Used dried ingredients for the rest. Still turned out great! Thank you!

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: I'm only giving 3 stars for this because although it was tasty, it wasn't an overwhelming hit, AND the recipe directions are not very good.  For one thing, the time to make - 28 minutes is a complete fallacy.  The recipe says to add all the ingredients and brown the potatoes - it doesn't give any clue of how long it will take, but I can tell you that I sautéed the potatoes for over 10 minutes, and they still were not brown.  At this point, I was up to 15-20 minutes of prep (all the chopping) and cook time.  I added the other ingredients (I used chicken stock as some other reviewers suggested, unfortunately, I did not read the review that said the recipe had too much liquid, and I added a hole can - 14oz - of stock).  It then took another 5 minutes to bring to a boil.  I set the timer for 5 minutes so I could uncover and stir.  When I checked after 5 minutes, now down to low, it didn't seem like the potatoes would cook.  After 10 minutes,  turned the heat back up.  When the 20 minutes were done, the potatoes had finally softened (I used red bliss), but, there was a lot of liquid left so I left the lid off and let it simmer another 10 minutes.  If you are keeping track, we are up to 55 minutes.  I finally added the cheese, and that seemed to make the liquid into more of a sauce, and the result was pretty good - very tasty, it reminded me of sausage and peppers that I make, and I ended up sopping up some of the gravy with bread - so very carb heavy meal.  I wish I could figure out a good vegetable to have with it (besides a salad).

name: sticken chicken
review: So easy!  Tender and delicious.  It's the first time in a very long time that my sweet baboo asked for seconds!  Definite keeper.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Thank you soooooo much!  I did a 13 lb pork shoulder in my 6 qt crock pot (it was packed) with 2 cups of ginger ale for 9 hours on low then added the BBQ sauce for anther 2 hours.  So freakin' easy and soooo delicious!  We had 19 people over, so thanks for making one part of the party easy ;)

name: frizzled cabbage
review: Second time making this.  The cooking level needs to be much lower and the amount of time cooked needs to by less than half as much even with a lower cooking level.  I would recommend more butter too.

name: kittencal s taco seasoning mix
review: I use it instead of store bought

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: This was amazingly good.  I followed your directions precisely, using fresh red peppers, skim milk, and mayo.  I doubled it and had enough to make a good size 9x13 pan full and I will have enough to have leftovers for dinner with salad tomorrow night.  I didn't add vegetables, as I always like to make the recipe as written the first time, but I could see where mixed vegetables would easily round out this meal and make it even more amazing.  The only thing I did do that was written was to season my chicken with seasoned salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder while cooking it.  I don't think that doing this really changed the outcome of the final result much at all.  This is definitely going into our favorite file.  Thank you so much Potsie!

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: Love oatmeal cookies, love peanut butter cookies.  These cookies are delicious and combine some great flavors.  Thank you!

name: better than sex cake iii
review: Tasty dessert that is liked by DH.  Thank you!

name: buttered egg noodles  best ever
review: Wonderful noodles.  We really enjoyed the egg noodles prepared this way.  Made as written but decreased the amount of butter used. Lovely noodles, buttery, creamy and delicious, full of flavor.  Served with Down East Oven Scallops and Roasted Sugar Snap Peas for a memorable meal.  Thank you so much for sharing this simple and easy to make treasure.

name: armenian herb marinade grilled chicken breasts
review: I made this after reading all the stellar reviews.  I was a bit disappointed.  I followed the recipe to the letter and it came out bland IMO.

name: softest ever bread machine bread
review: I usually make my bread by hand but I didnt want to heat up the kitchen and gave this recipe a shot. I thought my bread machine wasnt working right so after it set for 30 min I took it out and kneaded it by hand--put back in the machine just to let it sit and rise and after it rose I just selected bake. The bread is so good!!!  Great flavor, I think because of the salt content. Yum

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: Very tasty.  Cooked on high 3.5 hours.  Doubled the stuffing, After I took out the chicken I stirred the stuffing into the sauce.  Yummy  Very easy, I'll be making it again.  Thanks Anne!

name: bev s spaghetti sauce
review: I enjoyed this sauce.  Omitted the mushrooms (hate them) and took advice from reviewers on adding a bit of sugar.  I probably added a shake or 6 more of the spices because upon taste testing I couldn't find the flavors.  Sauce was simmered in the crock pot for 2 hours. Thank you so much for a good sauce recipe.  It will come in handy when I cannot find the jarred sauce.

name: rhubarb crisp
review: I'm sorry to say this but I'm really surprised at the amount of 5 stars given to this recipe. The 4 cups of rhubarb only filled  the 8x8 pan 1/4 of the way up the side in it's raw state. Once cooked there would have been maybe 1/2 an inch of filling. I went and cut 4 more stalks which gave me close to 7 cups and raised the rhubarb level to about 2/3 up the side of the pan and, of course, I need to increase the other ingredients that went into the filling. Also not mentioned in the recipe is a sitting time (30 mins for me) to allow the sugar (I used a sugar - Splenda mix -1/4 sugar to 3/4 Splenda) to draw out the juice. That's important because it keeps the filling from being dry and the thickened juice is an excellent part of a crisp. There is also way to much sugar in the topping for us so I used 1/4 cup Splenda Brown and 1/4 cup Splenda. I use Splenda because I'm diabetic but it measures and sweetens exactly like sugar and I would use the same changes if I were using sugar. With more rhubarb and less sweetner this make a dessert that we well enjoyed.

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: Delicious pancakes. Easy to make. I used a 1/3 cup measure and got 9 pancakes out of this recipe. I wrap them individually and put them in freezer bags. My mom can enjoy pancakes anytime she wants now. She either pops in the toaster or into the microwave.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Excellent. Left the chips out & served with both guacamole tortilla chips & flour tortillas so we could either dip or place in warmed tortilla, roll up & eat like a burrito. Served with sour cream & shredded lettuce. Thanks for sharing a nice twist on taco night!

name: salmon and asparagus in foil
review: I made this for dinner last night, leaving it in the oven for the full 18 minutes and it turned out perfectly cooked.  It was very easy and quick to make, healthy and satisfying and I loved that there was basically no washing up to do.  <br/><br/>Slightly lacking in flavour for me, but then I really like a sauce on fish and I didn't have any seasoning salt so used Italian herbs instead.  I served it with microwaved brown rice.<br/><br/>Will leave a rating after I try it with seasoning salt.

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: Great flavour, simple preparation.  I let the chicken marinate for 3 hours. Reduced the heat to 350F and it was done in the same amount of  time. I used a dark sesame oil which is very strong so I put in about 2 tsps of that and made up the rest with canola oil.  Even though I used low sodium soy sauce, I still found it very salty, so may reduce that or add a bit of water next time.  Thanks for a great recipe that I will be sure to use again.

name: chicken pot pie with 2 crusts
review: Same recipe I've made for years. I put some seasoning - celery salt, dill, whatever, in the crust. A family favorite.

name: vanilla scented granola
review: Yum!  What I really like about this is that it is kind of crispy and kind of chewy at the same time which makes for a perfect granola.  Made just as written but subbing coconut oil for the oil.  Thanks for the great recipe Bev.....

name: irish rosie s irish soda bread
review: Really quick and simple recipe to mix together and the loaf looked beautiful, a real show piece. The only change I would make next time would be to use only 1 T. of caraway seeds, just personal preference. This bread is wonderful toasted. Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: cinnamon sugar bread  bread machine
review: Not enough cinna or sugar flavor for me...even with adding some extra cinnamon.  If you are gonna make it, I'd suggest making this honey butter to go with it: http://www.food.com/recipe/honey-butter-17086

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: This made a quick and easy lunch.  It is a good recipe to have on hand for something quick. The eggs did not cover enough, especially if I were to add more vegetables.  If I make again, I will use 3 eggs.

name: real english fish and chips with yorkshire beer batter
review: 6-9-2104  As an update, we continue to use this recipe when ever we have fried fish.  Remains the best I've found.  As usual FT your recipe is a winner.  This is the first time I've tried to deep fry fish and this was sooooo good.  DGSs love fried anything, and this fit the bill for a quick and actually very easy dinner.  I didn't use the chips, just the battered fish and we loved it.  I followed the recipe and used my deep fryer to make.  Tasted so much like the fish we remeber and love in England on our visit.  I did use tilapia as that was all we had and it was great.  Can't thank you enough for posting a recipe my DGSs enjoyed as much as we did.

name: tortellini tomato spinach soup
review: Good but not delicious. It is simple as is, but put more in your bowl by simmering carrots, celery, and other veggies first. I also used fresh baby kale instead of spinach.

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: Great way to use fresh summer produce! I liked it, but thought it was a little too sweet for my taste. I would probably skip the sugar next time. Otherwise, it tastes like summer!

name: korean roast chicken thighs
review: I gave this 4 stars only because I prefer the skin to be more crisp. Otherwise it was VERY TASTY!!! Didn't have any green onion, so I used yellow onion. Will make this again, but will broil it a little just to crisp-up the skin. THANKS for sharing!!!

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: These are good but very mild.  The flavor reminds me of chicken ala king.

name: kale chips
review: I had Kale growing in my garden and wanted to find a healthier snack food while using my Kale and was pleased to find this recipe.  I too increased the vinegar and cut back on the salt.  Used the parchment paper and had no trouble with sticking.  The flavor took a little to get used to but after a few bites it really grows on you - and hey, the health factor is major.  Don't think it quite replaces potato chips but like that it still fills you up.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I doubled the ingredients for the sauce. I used garlic powder instead of garlic salt. And I also added about 1 teaspoon of sesame oil for flavor. After browning the chops in the pan on the stove top, I drained off all the fat, then added the sauce and reduced the temp to low, covered and cooked everything on the stove top for about 7-8 minutes until the pork tested done. I took the pork out of the pan and thickened the sauce with a cornstarch slurry, then put the pork chops back in the pan. We ate it over brown rice and it was fantastic. My guest loved it. This will make my regular rotation.

name: crock pot ravioli
review: This turned out ok for us. I only cooked it 3-4 hours and it still was too soft and the sauce started to burn. I left out the red pepper seasoning and used parmesan cheese.

name: kittencal s onion patties latkes
review: Update: Still delicious. Thick thick batter, I am not sure why a few have difficulty with it, use dry and wet measuring cups and the milk is just enough to moisten the batter. oh were these good. (are..im still eating them lol) Thanks so much for the recipe. Made for the zaar cookbooks game

name: kittencal s famous coleslaw
review: No words needed. Hands-down AWESOME!

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: I only made 1 c. of this dip but loved it.  Great with Flipsides.  Still have leftovers after using it as an appetizer.

name: slow cooked bbq ribs  for crock pot
review: We loved this simple, delicious way to prepare ribs. Tender, fall-off the bone meat. Used our favorite KC Masterpiece BBQ sauce. Finger-lickin' and lip-smackin' good. Thanks Dreamgoddess.

name: tsr 1993 version of cinnabon cinnamon rolls by todd wilbur
review: Just like Cinnabons, AMAZING! <br/><br/>I did most of the work the night before with my stand mixer. I rolled the dough and sliced it, putting the rolls on a large baking pan. Covered them with plastic wrap and put them in the fridge overnight. Woke up at 4am and put them out on the counter (turned the dishwasher on beneath them to aid in rising). Popped them in the oven at 6 and they were a delicious delightful treat for the family breakfast. <br/><br/>I did cut down the powdered sugar and butter (1.25 cups sugar, 5 tbs butter, 4 oz cream cheese) in the frosting and up the cream cheese because I am entirely addicted to cream cheese. Thanks so much for the keepr, Lightly Toasted!<br/><br/>*400 convection 15 minutes. Use all brown sugar.

name: banana banana bread
review: It came out alright.  The top carmelized to the point of near-burnt at 55 minutes.  Pick that off, it tastes better.  I was worried that if I took it out any sooner, the inside would be goo.<br/><br/>Moist enough, but lacking in spices in my opinion.  I dusted the top with cinnamon.<br/><br/>I'd modify, next time.  Add a generous amount of cardamom to the batter as it pairs quite well with banana.  I'd also add nuts of some sort.

name: berry smash muffins  strawberry muffins
review: Very easy to make and tasted pretty good. I also felt like there was something not quite right for my tastes, like they are missing something.

name: kittencal s buttery cut out sugar cookies w  icing that hardens
review: Good cookies & awesome icing to work with. A great pair!  Thanks!

name: bretzel rolls  bavarian pretzel sandwich rolls
review: I do think they are a better stand alone roll than a sandwich roll (the bread is too dense to manage a sandwich... it doesn't give and smooshes out the filling when you bite down).  5 stars anyway for being super delicious.  They were so good my kids wanted to make them the next day after we first tried them.  We made some of the dough into rolls and some into pretzels.  This recipe is way better than Costco's pretzel rolls (and I think Costco generally sells superior products).<br/><br/>The second time I made it, I added a scant 1/4 teaspoon of kosher salt to the dough.  We'll definitely make this again.<br/><br/>I agree that it might be better to bake them at 400 to avoid them getting a little too dark.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Very good!  Made just as directed.

name: potato kielbasa skillet
review: This was delicious!!  I couldn't find shredded American, so used six individual slices on top.  MizzNezz, thank you for another fantastic recipe!

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: My granddaughters and I ended up making 2 of these back to back because we had a lot of blueberries. I put vanilla in the batter the 1st time and on top the 2nd time. We actually liked it on top the best. Liked the hard sugary crust on top. I would like to try some of the variations the other reviews did also. Thanks for sharing!

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: Very good and flavorful. I made for our large family camping trip for our greek dinner.  I used small red potatoes, lots more garlic and chicken broth instead of water.  I think 1/2 the oil could have been used with great results. I lined the pan with foil, but wouldn't do that next time because the potatoes didn't stick, but the foil did.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: We used a little bit extra garlic and chicken broth instead of water as some others suggested and it worked great.

name: best oatmeal cookies
review: Very very good cookies! I made this recipe and brought some cookies to my office. Everybody loved it and they even emailed me telling me how delicious they were! I did made some minor adjustments - 1. I used only 1 cup of sugars in total (half cup of white sugar and half cup of brown sugar); 2. I substituted pecans with cashews because I didn't have any pecans on hand; 3. I made a few drop cookies as the recipe states. They were so moist and delicious. I also made some big flat ones by pressing the drop a little further. They turned out crispy. Loved both versions. Will be making these again for sure! Thank you for the amazing recipe!

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: This was really good, my DH loves lasagna and he said it was't the best he ever had, he prefers my original recipe that I use, but maybe it was due to me not having all of the ingredients.  I didn't have as much cottage cheese as it called for and it definitely could have been a little cheesier.  I would definitely make it again.

name: easy banana muffins
review: These were delicious and enjoyed by my kids for breakfast.  They had great flavor and very moist.  I subbed applesauce for the butter.  Thank you!

name: beth s pizza crust
review: This is the only pizza crust recipe I use anymore.  It is quick, easy, and turns out right as long as you make sure to prebake it long enough.  Last time I made it I didn't let it bake long enough and then even though I baked it again with toppings on it came out a little soggy.  I like it with the Italian herbs in it.

name: hamburger noodle bake
review: This is a good old classic hamburger casserole.  I think my mom made it growing up.  I always have hamburger in my freezer so this is a good go to recipe when I need something quick.

name: blueberry oatmeal muffins
review: We devoured these for breakfast.  I really liked the oatmeal for texture and fiber it added.  We will make these again, thank you!

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: This sauce is the bomb. Quick, easy to make and it tastes great.  So much better than store bought.  It was perfect served with chicken wings and burgers.  I can`t wait to try it on bbq steak.  The sauce is sweet, spicy, hot and delicious. Thank you so much for sharing.

name: quick and easy pizza dough
review: Wow, what a great recipe.  It was so quick and easy to make, with ingredients always found in the pantry.  It rose beautifully and tasted great.  I made half the batch and it made two nice size pizzas.  I added pizza sauce, herbs, sweet onion, red peppers, pepperoni, green olives and lots of cheese for a delicious meal.  Cooked on the bottom rack of my convection oven, it worked great.  Thanks so much for sharing this recipe, which I will be making often.

name: long john silver s fish batter
review: We didn't care for this at all.  I prepared fish and onions rings and they soaked up so much oil. I used vegetable oil, (type to use wasn't listed in ingredients), kept the temp at 375 degrees, and fried in small batches.  It wasn't that I was trying to duplicate the LJS fish,  just attempting to get the crunchiness and little 'crunchies'.  Sorry to rate so low, as I was very hopeful and then disappointed.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: This was the first time I have ever made chocolate frosting...I usually get store-bought. This was so much better! I made it to go on yellow cupcakes my husband requested for his birthday. Thank you for sharing!

name: cheese and garlic drop biscuits
review: I was glad to find this recipe that did not use Bisquick, since I never have it on hand.  Very good, next time I will double or triple the recipe to freeze and have on hand :)

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Easy to make and a big hit. Will definitely make again. Thanks for sharing.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: Great simple muffin.  I cut the sugar in half and added extra blueberries and the muffins came out great. I left off the topping.  Thanks for sharing.

name: cha ching  carrot spice muffins
review: I didn't have raisins or nuts, and thought that these could be a tad sweeter (if making without raisins); spreading cream cheese on them seemed to improve the lack of sweetness. I usually decrease the sugar in recipes but found this one did not need that. Overall, a good muffin. Thanks for sharing!

name: the cheesecake factory pumpkin cheesecake by todd wilbur
review: So good! Pumpkin cheesecake is my favorite cheesecake and this is an excellent recipe. Easy too!

name: kittencal s onion patties latkes
review: I needed to find a way to use up masses of green onions I chopped for anther recipe, but didn't use. I've made these exactly as written before and have them 5 stars. Decided I could use kittencals recipe as a base. So, used all green onions, and all I had was rice milk, so that's what I used. I had a little cold white rice in the fridge, so just sprinkled 1/4 cup in too. Followed the rest of the recipe as written. It was great. Might just use rice milk again and save a few calories! Hee hee..not that a few calories will matter in this wonderful fried recipe.

name: creamy garlic penne pasta
review: Amazing.  I used evaporated D Milk because I had some on hand, but otherwise did exactly as recipe stated. Perfect side dish to round out any meal.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: I followed the directions but did not cook it down as much as directed. It was too thick even before I started cooking it down. The flavor was good but I need a smoother sauce--mine was like paste. I cant make this recipe again without changes and like it

name: tsr version of red lobster cheddar bay biscuits by todd wilbur
review: I haven't been to Red Lobster in probably 10 years but these biscuits taste just like I remember them.  Daughter loved them too.  Thank you!

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: I had a surplus of cherry tomatoes this year, and tried this recipe.  WOW.  They not only make a wonderful presentation, they are delish!  Thank you Merlot!

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: This is a superb recipe! The meat was so tender and the stew very flavorful. I cut way back on the onion (don't tolerate it very well) and added extra celery. Served with biscuits, it makes a warm and hearty winter meal.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Made this just as it is written.  For the "favorite" barbeque sauce we used Dinosaur, a locally famous sauce from the Syracuse NY area.  Lots of leftovers. So we will freeze it for another meal.  Thanks for the easy crock pot recipe!

name: gumbo
review: Absolutely fantastic! Very simple to make and once all the veggies are chopped and the roux is done it goes very quickly. I halved the dish since it's just 2 of us but it only ended up being about 3 servings. Next time I'll make the full recipe. I used a lot more of the Cajun seasoning (probably about 2 tsp) and added about 1 tsp of File powder. I also used chopped andouille and shrimp. This was really, really unexpected how great this was.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Outstanding. I used rotisserie chicken and well-seasoned chicken broth. The filling was creamy and nothing but delicious. This was much easier to make than my gran's recipe and tastes just as good (maybe better). My fam and I love comfort food and I will definitely make this again. Thanks for sharing this recipe.

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: Very good salad. I used shallots instead of green onions and shredded pepperjack cheese. I also added some sugared nuts. The dressing tastes very light and tangy. I used red wine vinegar.  Thanks for posting!

name: angel food cake   homemade
review: Very light, fluffy, and totally delicious!  I especially appreciated the detailed instructions as I used the recipe to help someone make their first ever angel food cake.  The cake was terrific and made lasting memories of cooking with a friend. Thank you for sharing this keeper of a recipe!

name: awesome blueberry muffins
review: Ugh. I had high hopes for these muffins with all the great reviews. But their was so much topping and it was just so heavy, the muffins completely sank in the middle. The muffins overflowed in the pan and all stuck together creating one big mess. What a disaster.

name: kittencal s chocolate frosting icing
review: Made the dark version, and doubled for a thicker frosting on my 9x13 cake. This is fantastic; rich and creamy. It makes you understand what your parents and grandparents mean when they say the canned icing doesn't taste like the things their parents made when they were kids. Kittencal's recipes are awesome. Thanks for sharing.

name: dark chocolate cake
review: Wonderful! Used the 3/4 boiling water as recommended and it was perfect. Hubby wanted chocolate cake for his birthday and I'm anti box mixes. Slathered this in Kittencal's dark chocolate butter cream frosting off this site. Rich dark chocolate perfection. Thanks for sharing. My husband thanks you as well!

name: thai chicken breasts
review: I grilled the chicken and prepared the sauce separately, adding about 1 T. of cornstarch to thicken.  I served over an Asian salad.  It was delicious!

name: the very best salisbury steak
review: I liked this recipe.  My husband loved it.  Since he is the family Salisbury Steak expert, I gave the recipe 5 stars.  I made it in my 10" cast iron pan.  The patties got a nice crisp crust.  The meat was very, very tender. I served it with mashed potatoes.

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: Nice casserole!  DH loved it.

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: Loved this - will make often.  I did use onions instead of shallots.  May try basil next time, but I liked it with the rosemary.

name: easy garlic chicken
review: This was originally 3*, but on the second nite I heated it up, and it was better, so probably 3 1/2*.  I followed the recipe exactly.  I may make it again.  Not sure yet.

name: microwave chocolate mug brownie
review: this was very chocolaty and very easy! I used milk instead of water. Next time I might decrease the sugar. Enough for 2 to share!

name: mahogany beef stew
review: I absolutely love the flavor of this stew.  It is rich and satisfying.  I add some small pasta and it takes it to a whole new level.  Thanks for posting this.  It is my go to beef roast recipe.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I'll just add my 5 stars to this easy recipe.  Needed something to go with my homemade pretzel rolls and this sounded so easy it was perfect.  Followed the directions and even my picky grandkids loved it after tasting and didn't leave a bit on the plate.

name: mashed red potatoes with garlic and parmesan
review: Very tasty and really easy, too! I added a little extra milk. Garlic flavor is not strong, so could add more if desired. We enjoyed it as is. Thanks for the recipe!

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: I have not had any sugar in 10 days, but we are having Fall like weather so I wanted to bake something. These are really good. I used a blend of sugar and Stevia for the 1/2 cup. A sprinkle of brown sugar in the mix. Then added a sprinkle of brown sugar on the top of each one. Trying to cut the sugar but they tasted like they had a lot of sugar but I think that is due to my hyatias.

name: slow cook down home pork chops and gravy
review: My husband and I really liked this dish. I didn't have dry mustard, so I rubbed my chops with a little grainy Dijon mustard before I dredged them in the flour. I like mustard and pork together anyway. I liked the ease of this recipe, too. I served with mashed red skin potatoes, and steamed carrots. Perfect meal!

name: 40 minute hamburger buns
review: I made these buns tonite and they were a hit with us!  After reading most of the reviews, I decided to decrease the oil and sugar, both to 3 tablespoons, as others suggested.  I was nearly out of yeast; I only had 1 tablespoon, but I went with just the one.  When I rolled the dough into balls, I flattened them out in my hand before putting them on the baking sheet.  I wanted a larger hamburger bun.  I let the dough rise for about 40 minutes and then baked them at 375 degrees since a few reviewers complained of the bottoms being too brown.  After 17 minutes in the oven, they were picture perfect brown on top.  The bottoms were perfect too.  When I sliced them open I was amazed at the texture & fragrance.  I know I made some changes to the amounts on ingredients, but I love this recipe.  It makes beautiful burger buns.  I plan to use this recipe again really soon and maybe try making cinnamon rolls.  Thank you so much for posting this  recipe.

name: kittencal s fluffiest scrambled eggs
review: I felt silly using a recipe for scrambled eggs, but these are really so much better than my usual of throwing together some eggs and milk.  I will use this recipe from now on!

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: Fabulous fresh flavors with a little heat. Loved it.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: Great technique for cooking corn.  We enjoyed it and the amazing thing was no prep work was involved, also the silk wasn't a pain to get out either.  Thank you!

name: pasta with sausage  tomatoes  and cream
review: Very quick and easy weeknight meal. I used bow tie pasta and subbed in fresh basil, from my garden, for the parsley. :)

name: steak  or chicken  fajitas
review: We really wanted to like these more, considering all of the great reviews. And I hate being the one to spoil that "streak". :-(  But we found these to be too hot (and we normally like spicy foods) and lacking the authentic fajita flavors reminiscent of Mexican restaurants. All that came through was the heat, and the lime juice sort of just faded out. Unfortunately, we probably won't be making them again, and revert to using Todd Wilbur's recipe, but it was fun trying something new.

name: quick yellow cake
review: I have never left a one star review before, I did not read the reviews prior to making this cake, just looked at the number of reviews and the 4 1/2 star rating out of 162 reviews.  I made it to take to church and was so ashamed of it. It looked like cornbread and that is what I called it after it was cut at church.  Now I see others have thought the same thing.  Why this cake has this many good reviews is beyond me.  Already throw recipe away, will not be making again.  I am sorry for the review but it is the truth.

name: kittencal s italian zucchini mozzarella patties
review: I prefer to bake these in the oven at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Well, I must add my raves to the many many other reviewers of this cake!  I have many frozen bananas that I just popped in the freezer when they got too ripe to eat, and wanted to use some up.  I made this recipe and got raves from the family, already requesting that I make it again, so you can be sure I will do that!!  I will turn some into banana bread by following the recipe, but cutting the sugar just a little.  What a great recipe, thanks so much for posting it, Rhonda J!!!!

name: simple tomato sandwich
review: I have been eating  these for more years than I want to say.  We always grow tomatoes in the summer, and this is my favorite way to eat them...I love mine on fresh bread, not toasted with or without cheese.  Must be best foods Mayo..  It's a race between my hubbie and I for the first tomato of the season for a fresh tomato sandwich.

name: best ever tuna noodle casserole
review: I've made a lot of tuna casseroles and have to say this is the best.  So simple but such a nice creamy flavor.  I added a can of cream of celery and topped with the cheddar cheese.  What a great and quick recipe when you need something fast.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: Made this at a special request.  Turned out soft, chewy and cinnamon sweetness.  Loved them and easy to make.

name: chunky blue cheese salad dressing
review: First time I ever made this and it is the BEST.  Love the flavors, no wonder it has so many wonderful reviews.  Makes a lot, so be prepared.

name: roast  sticky  chicken
review: Delicious roast chicken. Perfectly seasoned, skin crisp, meat tender. Made exactly as directed, no changes. Thanks.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: Yummy and so easy to put together. Next time I will add a little more brown sugar

name: traditional tamales  pork
review: I have tried other recipes,but this is the bomb..As others have stated, alot of work,but so worth it...I doubled the sauce recipe so I could freeze half for next time, I make these.I used ancho and guajillo peppers. Nice smoky flavor..I dont have the corn hush rolling down yet,mine looked like torpedos,but they sure tasted great..Cant thank you enough for this recipe....

name: dad s casserole
review: Wow this was good. Have had it before with cottage cheese for the cream cheese but I think this way is even better. Excellent- thanks!

name: divine meatball sandwiches
review: I just finished preparing and eating these sandwiches.  Made with meatball recipe #69173.  My daughter loved the addition of the cream cheese mixture.  I, on the other hand, couldn't really taste it.  May be that I didn't spread on enough??  I have a lot of it left over.  Now to find another use for it, becasue I hate waste. Thank you for the recipe.

name: meatball sub casserole
review: Great dish for our church potluck. Very very tasty! Thanks!

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Very good!  I added dried onion to the mixture simply because we love onion.  I was hesitant to add the raw balls to the sauce because I don't care for meat with a meatloaf texture nor do I care for grease in the sauce.  Therefore, I browned them a bit beforehand.  Thank you for the recipe!

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Okay, this is a true keeper indeed. I was looking for a really good "comfort food" dish to take to my dear elderly neighbors (he's quite ill) and came across this. Oh! Just a warm big fat pie of love! The one change I made: subbing a diced sweet potato for the white potato. Don't laugh! I had to do it, or run to the store. And surprise: it was fabulous! I omitted the carrot, so the sweet potato gave the needed color, and the taste was wonderful.  great recipe!

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: Count me among the fans of this famous chicken salad. I made one very minor change in that I used mayonnaise instead of miracle wip as I do not care for miracle wip. I used smoked chicken and thought the light smoky flavor went great with the grapes. Thanks for a recipe that will now be a staple in our house.

name: french toast sticks   oamc
review: We haven't had a chance to freeze these yet, but they were a big hit straight out of the oven.  I did 1 1/2 batches of batter, and got almost 12 slices out of it.  I used french bread, cut into 1" slices, with each slice cut into thirds.  I used parchment paper, and turned them carefully with a spatula - no problems sticking.  I baked them a bit longer than 25 minutes.  We had them for "night breakfast" with sausage and grapefruit.  We're looking forward to reheating the leftovers for breakfast.  Thanks for sharing! (Also, I've never added the butter, and we haven't missed it a bit!)

name: ciabatta  italian slipper bread
review: I love this bread.  So good and really pretty simple to make,  I made the dough in the ABM and then took out, shaped and baked.  The dough was so silky and easy to work with and the end results with a crusty outside but soft, fluffy center.  When baking in the oven I sprayed the bottom of the oven with water every 5 minutes X3 for that nice crust.  Served it in slices with oil and balsamic vinegar for dipping.  So nice - will continue to use this recipe for sure and strongly recommend

name: chinese buffet style donuts
review: Ridiculously easy and delicious!!! I did EXACTLY what the recipe states and I was so surprised how good these turned out! Thank you for the amazing recipe!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: What can I possibly say that hasn't already been said?  Just delicious!  I made this exactly as posted, except I opted to make 2 pot pies, rather than 1 large one.  Fortunately, I had two 10-inch pie plates, but I bet 9-inch deep-dish would work too.  The filling was very generous and was the perfect ration of filling to crust.  We are enjoying this greatly, and will probably freeze the second pie for the future!  Thanks for sharing this lovely recipe.  Made for Culinary Quest 2014.

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: Delicious! My only change was to leave out the fennel because I didn't have any. Simmered this the full hour. I doubled for 3 pizzas and have some left to freeze for another time. Thanks for sharing.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: Fantastic! Everyone ate their plates clean, even the fussiest that doesn't like anything but<br/>peanut butter. Thank you for sharing.

name: cube steak and gravy  crock pot
review: Made as directed only doing following changes;<br/><br/>Brown gravy mix instead of onion gravy mix.  3T onion flakes, 2 onions sliced thin and garlic powder. <br/>Cooked 6-7 hours on high.  Was not mushy like other reviewers stated.  BF loved it!<br/>Served with mashed potatoes and sautéed mushrooms.  Will make again.<br/>The smell while cooking was incredible!!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: Yum! I was craving some great comfort food and this was it! Very simple and good. I used refrigerated pie crusts and this came together very quickly. Thanks for sharing this nice winner, breezermom. Made for Culinary Quest 2014.

name: perfect southern fried chicken
review: Oh boy, oh boy!  We really enjoyed this fried chicken even though I made a mess with the paper bag and all, so won't be making it that way again.  Perhaps its because I used very large thighs.  Whatever.  This cooked up perfectly crunchy on the outside and tender and juicy on the inside.  I don't have Season All, so just made up my own mix with Adobo Seasoning and Sazon I make myself.  We don't have fried chicken often since its not supposed to be all that healthy, but this is a great recipe when you want to splurge and treat yourself to some real comfort food.  CQ

name: vanilla scented granola
review: Great recipe!  I have made it several times and it always turns out perfect.  I substituted walnuts for the almonds the first time I made it.  We liked it so much that I have used walnuts every time.  Thanks for the great granola recipe!  So easy and delicious!

name: easy creamy sour cream chicken casserole
review: So easy to be so good.  I did a few things different - sauted the chicken pieces with onions and garlic, and after spreading the chicken in the casserole dish topped with fresh corn kernels.  Topped with cheddar cheese prior to the crackers and then baked.  Oh so creamy good.  What a winning recipe.  Enjoyed by all and have plenty left over for another night which is a good thing.

name: pan grilled pork chops
review: Thanks, DH just loved this and it was so easy!  I used pork cube steak which can be a little tricky, but this way turned out just great.

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: I used Recipe #392583 for the chickpeas and then cooked them again for the three hours stated.  Loved all the spices, just used half a recipe for 2 thighs and half the cayenne.  Will make more next time.

name: mama s supper club tilapia parmesan
review: Delicious! Fancy and fast!  Thanks so much.

name: the sweetest blueberry muffins
review: DELICIOUS!!!  I did use 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup ff greek yogurt, used coconut sugar - 2/3 cup and half whole wheat flour. I also just topped with turbinado sugar because I was in a hurry. They were delicious!!!  Probably the best blueberry muffins I have made!! Mmmm.

name: southwestern baked spaghetti
review: We loved this casserole. Easy to assemble, delicious flavor. Perfect weeknight meal. Thanks.

name: perfect southern fried chicken
review: This was yummy fried chicken. I absoutely loved the cooking method (lid on first 5 min on each side)! It worked like a charm. I used Paula Deen's recipe for her seaoned salt for the Season All. The only change I would make next time is to eliminate the cornmeal. I didn't care for that added texture. Personal preference only! Thank you! Made for the International Agents of QUEST for Culinary Quest US Southern Region.

name: basil pesto
review: A good way to use the abundance of basil in my garden!  I used 4 cloves of garlic and added a tablespoon or so more olive oil as well as a sprinkling of salt.

name: baked ziti
review: This was a good basic ziti recipe.  It was cheesy and creamy and easy!  I left out the meat and added sauteed mushrooms and cauliflower.  Turned out great except next time I'll season the parts a little more.  Thanks for the great recipe S in PA...

name: cajun style oven fries
review: These were really yummy! I served them with my homemade fry sauce.

name: chicago italian beef
review: Out of this world goodness!!!

name: milk free  egg free pancakes
review: batter's pretty thin by my experience with other recipes but good enough for an eggless milkless recipe and therefore an acceptable backup when Im out of milk and eggs...I *did* make changes but they did not affect the basic chemistry of the recipe...changes I made are as follows...1tb extra sugar as I prefer a sweeter batter, 3tb oil instead of margarine as I feel oil works better, eliminated water substitute indicated for egg although next time I may decrease the primary water ingredient as well for a thicker batter...thanks for posting this recipe!

name: perfect southern fried chicken
review: To be clear from the start, this is fabulous and we loved it. That said, there's no substitute for Mama's love and experience, and I think this would have been better yet with some practice. The flour mixture in the bag quickly became dough and was replaced with a 9x9 pan of it. The chicken pieces we used were huge, and getting it to cook through without being too dark and crunchy was a challenge met only on the second batch through, so counter to my natural greed, I suggest you work with a smaller chicken. Once we got through all that, we got delicious, rich, moist-to-the-bone-and-crunchy-outside gen-you-wine fried chicken and at the risk of repeating, loved it.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: This is definitely one of the better taco casseroles I've tried. I only had to bake it for about 10 minutes, which kept the chips from getting soggy.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: We enjoyed this dish.  I marinated the beef in the sauce mixture using all regular soya and skipped the dredging process.  I made a second batch of sauce using teriyaki sauce.  I found it less salty than the regular soya sauce and I didn't have the reduced sodium type. I tossed in some onion as well because we love onion.  This came out so close to what we usually order at our little Chinese restaurant.  Thank you so much for the recipe.  Sure helps when we have a craving for Chinese and don't feel like going to the city.

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: OMG!!! was this terrific. I used red seedless grapes and pecans. I did roast the pecans before adding them. It looked so tasty and tasted yummy. It was hot the day when I served this and it was a wonderful summer dish. Thank you so much for posting it. I will diffidently be making this again.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Made this tonight using a fresh jalapeno, tomatoes and cilantro from the garden.  So good. It's like all the yummy stuffing from our favorite burrito shop, but in a bowl. The whole family enjoyed this.

name: beer  n bbq braised country style pork ribs
review: Gosh I love this dish - I have made it several times. We always look forward to leftovers.

name: wonderful salsa
review: Wow! I will never buy commercial salsa again! I used fresh cherry and roma tomatoes, jalapenos, and bell peppers from my garden. The flavor is amazing. This is great with black beans and corn added (although I'm not sure it's safe to can with them). I only add about half the cumin, and I never peel the tomatoes. Thank you!

name: black bean and tortilla bake
review: Very good... modify the bean/sauce mixture until it tastes the way you want it. As is, I didn't think there was enough flavor. I added some salsa and also smoked paprika, more chili powder, and a Chipotle spice mix. This is the first tortilla casserole I've made that holds its layers when cut- yet with the extra salsa I didn't think it was too dry, either.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Very Easy to make. This recipe was approved by my family.  I used more sugar to offset the intensiveness of the vinegars.  Made for Culinary Quest 2014.

name: beef barley soup
review: SO SO SO SO FREAKING GOOD! Other than fresh vegetables stated in the recipe, I also added a cup of frozen mix veggies. Instead of cooking on low for 10-12 hours, I set my crock pot on high and the wonderful soup was ready after 6 hours! My entire house smelled like heaven. My DH couldn't wait. He went check on the soup pretty much once every hour while it's being cooked. Must cook!! Thanks a ton for this awesome recipe!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Very good balsamic salad dressing, it pleased most people at dinner (it could be that the one person who didn't like it as much just doesn't like balsamic vinegar, because I used a very good quality aged balsamic vinegar).  I was happy to have some leftover for my lunch.  Thank you for sharing this recipe, Mrs. Goodall!  Made for Culinary Quest.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: One word says it all - delicious!  It's easy and quick to make with ingredients I typically have on hand.  You can't beat that!  Made for Culinary Quest 2014.

name: parmesan zucchini
review: Wonderful recipe! Will be using this recipe for our zucchini from now on- thanks!

name: panera broccoli cheese soup
review: We don't know what Panera's soup taste like because we've never been there.  We DO know that this was a tasty soup.  I only had 1c. half and half and used evaporated milk to make up the difference. I used mild cheddar.  We did not find this to taste like cheese dip, did not find the nutmeg overpowering, and had no problem with the texture.  I'd say this is a 'keeper'.  Thank you!

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: What a delicious summer dish. It couldn't be easier. I just layered everything in the crockpot and let it cook away. It came out perfect. I actually used this as a pizza topping which was a hit in our household. This is a great way to use up all of the great produce that's available in the summer. This will be made again and thanks for posting!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: This was a great dressing to use on a simple tossed salad. Full of fresh flavor that we liked very much! Will have to make sure I always have this dressing in the fridge. Made and reviewed for Culinary Quest 2014 - Cruisin' Culinary Queens.

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: Great!  To make it easier for myself I put all of the spices, onion and Italian spices into the mayo about an hour before to let the flavors blend.  I added the coated slices to the cookie sheet of veggies I was roasting.  Everything turned out fantastic!  I did flip the slices at the 12 minute interval as well as toss the roasted veggies.  I used a parchment lined baking sheet and everything came out perfect.  Thanks.

name: ratatouille in the crock pot
review: This was great, I had all these things in my garden and what a nice way to use them up.  I then made a lasagna type dish with this.  I put home made spaghetti sauce in the bottom of rectangle casserole dish put some uncooked egg noodles in the bottom on top of the sauce then the ratatouille then added cottage cheese which I mixed with parmesan and mozzarella cheese then sprinkled more noodles topped with more sauce then cheese, oh man to die for.  My daughter the vegetarian said I had outdone myself.

name: crock pot garlic brown sugar chicken
review: WOW!  Only change was a can of Vernor's as I didn't have Sprite or 7-up!  That was the first time!  Second time I used Vernor's but added chunks of sweet bell peppers, (multi-colored) and chunks of Vidalia onion.  I cooked two thighs and halfway through added a boneless/skinless chicken breast.  This was done in the oven at 350 degrees for a total of 45 minutes.  I can't say enough about this recipe, we love it!  Thanks.

name: basil pesto
review: Made just as directed, except used slightly less lemon (a splash, instead of 1/8 C), and a little more olive oil (to the desired consistency) as I didn't want too much lemon flavor.  It was perfect, and I think we've found our go-to basil pesto recipe! :)

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These are great meatballs, very flavourful. Great to make ahead and freeze. A great, reliable family meal.

name: pumpkin cake bars with cream cheese frosting
review: I chose this recipe because I really wanted something sweet with the canned pumpkin I found, and all ingredients I had on hand.  I decided to make cupcakes because I didn't want a huge cake and cupcakes are easier to ship off to the neighbors' houses. (I didn't need 24 cupcakes in my house!) I tested the batter and discovered that I too would add nutmeg and cloves for it to taste like my mother's pumpkin pies.  These were delicious!  I am not a baker in any way.  I never bake.  Hate to bake. So I don't know where I went wrong to cause the paper cups to be soaked in oil.
