This wasn't a problem for the final outcome of the cakes, but frustrating for me that the cupcakes wouldn't come completely out of the cups.  They may have looked ugly, but boy were they good!  Thank you for your recipe.  I will attempt the cake version next time.

name: lazy slow cooker creamy chicken noodle soup
review: This was a very healthy way to use up leftover roast chicken! I used cream of chicken soup and added some mushrooms. Like others, I added pasta 30 minutes before the end of cooking rather than cooking it separately, purely to make things easier. I liked that my son (10 months old) was able to eat with us as everything was nice and soft. For this reason I didn't add any seasoning. Thanks for a keeper!<br/>UPDATE: I made this again, adding 2 chopped parsnips and they gave the soup a lovely sweetness. I'll definitely do this again!

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: Excellent dressing!! Great flavor combo and it was perfect on our salad tonight. Now I'm bummed that I only made half a batch! Tomorrow is another day. ;-)  Made for Culinary Quest - Italy - International Agents of Quest. Thank you!

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: This recipe reminds me of my grandmother's fried pork chops w/ gravy. I followed the recipe exactly as written and it was outstanding. Moist tender chops with scrumptious gravy. Some effort is involved, but it is so worth it. Definitely will add this to my top-fav comfort foods list. Thanks for posting this one.

name: oven fried eggplant  aubergine
review: This was really great! I have only made eggplant a couple of times. I did salt the eggplant first (I googled it), and used panko bread crumbs - they do make it crispier I think. I also used parchment on the cookie sheet and had zero problems with sticking. When I flipped them I sprayed the tops again with spray to get them even more brown. I used 1/2 lite mayo and 1/2 greek yogurt, plus watered it down a bit so it went on smoothly. I also needed more breadcrumb mixture than this made - basically doubled it. Crispy on the outside and creamy on the inside!!!

name: simple tomato sandwich
review: I started making these because I was hungry for a BLT but had no B or L.  For me toasted bread is better because it soaks up the juices.

name: throw away the bread machine instructions      white bread
review: This is the easiest bread to put together! I did follow my bread machine instructions (I think it's ingrained in my head) and used all butter, no oil. I also used regular white flour (subbing 3 teaspoonfuls with 3 teaspoons of wheat gluten) I used the 'dough' setting on my machine, and ended up with TWO loaves because the first rise was a big rise, let rise for the second time, and followed previous reviews by baking at 350 for 25 minutes. I think I will bake a little longer next time as mine were still fairly light. But still, they were beautiful loaves, great texture, soft yet chewy. Can't wait to use them for sandwiches!! I think this may be a staple recipe in this house now. Thank you for another amazing recipe!

name: brown sugar meatloaf
review: I'm such a fan of yooper's recipes, how could I have missed this one?  So easy & simple, yet the best meatloaf I've ever made.  Well formed and tasty.  I used sweet chili sauce instead of catsup.  Gave the meat a nice tang.  I've finally found a meatloaf recipe that will be made more than once...thanks for yet another good recipe, yooper.

name: shirley s perfect rare roast beef
review: I was very skeptical of this so I baked my 1.5 lb roast for 15 minutes and followed the rest of the directions. It came out medium and so juicy (though the onions were still raw - I will slice them quite thin next time). I was so impressed! So very easy! I did salt and pepper my roast ahead of time - salt is important to make the meat taste good! I'll be making this recipe lots.

name: romano s macaroni grill rosemary bread
review: I made the dough in the bread machine and then shaped, allowed a 2nd rise and baked in the oven.  Sprinkled the top with the extra Rosemary and sea salt and it turned out great.  I love the flavor of the Rosemary and  the salt gave it an extra flavor that we enjoyed.  Next time though I think I'll use the egg wash instead of the extra butter as I like the shine I get from that.  As an update:  Continue to use this awesome recipe, my family likes it served with a dipping sauce of olive oil and balsamic vinegar with Italian herbs.  Never a piece left over

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: So very delicious!  I used frozen cauliflower,  low fat sour cream, and only one green onion.  It came perfect!  I will definitely make this again!

name: wonderful salsa
review: This turned out very good although I think next time I'll increase the jalapenos even more. I used a generous cup of chopped jalapenos (plus about half the removed seeds) and while the salsa tasted plenty spicy (medium/hot) after cooking, it mellowed out quite a bit after canning to more of a mild (my 2 year old was eating it). Next time I'll probably throw in an extra 2-3 jalapenos plus more seeds and I think it'll be perfect. Oh I also added the juice of 3 limes and omitted the sugar as my tomatoes were plenty sweet. Very easy to make! Thanks!

name: tsr version of carrabba s bread dipping spice by todd wilbur
review: Perfect dipping sauce for warm crusty bread.  I like CourtneyMiller0220's idea of using all fresh herbs.  Will try that next.  Thanks for sharing!

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: I make this often.  It is good and perfect as written.

name: chinese pot stickers
review: I love pot stickers, but my local store stopped carrying the pot stickers that were so, so, so tasty! I don't know what I did wrong with this recipe. I dislike how STRONG fresh ginger is, so I used ground ginger, but I doubt that would make the difference given how I feel about the overpowering taste of fresh ginger (I just can't grate or mince it small enough not to feel bowled over). I felt there was too much meat, too. (To be fair, I generally like most recipes better after I halve the meat and double the veggies.) I did finish this batch, but I won't make this recipe again because it just didn't have the over-the-moon flavor from my favorite but now unavailable pot stickers that I was looking for.

name: thai grilled chicken thighs
review: We loved this!  Fast and easy way to dress up a meal.  Delicious.  Thanks.

name: chocolate chocolate chip sour cream banana bread
review: Very nice recipe!  Made basically as written it comes out moist and flavorful!  Only thing I would say is that it doesn't have hardly any banana flavor so I'd like to bump that up next time.  But tastes like a really yummy chocolate cake!  Thanks for the great recipe Miss Diggy....

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: Family and I enjoyed this casserole. I used chopped tomatoes with chipotle and that added a slight  smokey flavor to the tangy sauce. Thanks for sharing.

name: salmon and asparagus in foil
review: What a simple, healthy, fast and  good meal.  Perfect for a weeknight. Made for the Culinary Quest 2014.

name: yummy crunchy apple pie
review: This recipe doesn't need any more reviews, but I'll add that I made 2, they were excellent & baking time ended up being a little longer. Allow the pie to cool before cutting.

name: cauliflower popcorn   roasted cauliflower
review: This was a hit at our house!  I cut my florets smaller than ping pong ball--but also roasted at 450 and cut the time to about 30 minutes.  I salted per the directions and did not need to add extra (and I do like salt).  I will definitely be making this again--though maybe a double batch on two jelly roll pans as we all would've enjoyed having more!

name: ground beef stuffed green bell peppers with cheese
review: Lovely dish.  I haven't had this in ages.  As a little girl, I don't remember liking this. Thankfully, my taste buds have matured, as I found this incredibly tasty.  Personally, I would have give this 5 stars, but I was outvoted by my family.  Thanks for a great recipe..I will no doubt be making this again!<br/>Update 9/7/14:  I used grated, fresh cauliflower in place of rice to make this more low-carb friendly and enjoyed the texture that the cauliflower gave to the dish.  I simply added the cauliflower along with drained diced tomatoes and left out the water...and baked according to recipe.  Enjoyed it very much!

name: tomato and basil bruschetta
review: I used cherub tomatoes and they were great.  Loved the balsamic with the tomatoes and the toasted bread.  Did the bread in the oven 400 for 10 min.

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Very good!  I had a little over 1 1/2 lb of ground meatloaf mix.  Added egg, pepper, small diced onion, ketchup. Instead of the bread, I added 2 nice sized handful of StoveTop stuffing and only added 1/3 cup of milk.  Sprinkled a little sea salt over the top as well as a very small sprinkle of a Garlic Garlic seasoning I had on hand.  Cooked at 375 for 1 hour then for another 10 to 12 min at 425 (because I added biscuits to oven to be cooked at higher temp).  I did not add the topping, as we don't like our meatloaf too sweet and it already had ketchup inside and I like to serve with brown gravy, which I did.  Very much enjoyed by my 14 y/o son and myself.  Not too salty, moist inside, a little browned on the top and just enough of every ingredient for a flavorful meatloaf...just the way we like it.  Thanks for posting, will make again!

name: monastery lentils
review: Very nice flavors! We all enjoyed this. I served this over brown rice and with a grilled chicken. I only used 3 TBS of the oil and for the canned tomatoes I used fire roasted. Next time I'll add some chopped fresh spinach, it was crying out for it. Absolutely use the fresh parsley, and even add more because of that great fresh taste. Don't  know why you'd need the cheese on top, though. Perhaps that's just personal taste. Thanks Belkathy for a great recipe I can use all year long!

name: kittencal s easy tuna or chicken noodle casserole
review: Another winner by Kitten.  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s easy and delicious ranch parmesan chicken
review: Another fantastic recipe from Kittencal! This was so easy to make and so so yummy.

name: basil pesto
review: I liked the lemon flavour of this. It also used a lot less oil than other recipes. Tasted great with pasta!

name: gumbo
review: This was my first attempt at gumbo and never having eaten it before I didn't know hat to expect.  It turned out very good!  I used shrimp for the meat.

name: kittencal s famous greek salad
review: This is a very good Greek salad!

name: my family s favorite sloppy joes  pizza joes
review: My family loved this. I made as directed except for the following: I didn't have celery, so I used a medium-sized green pepper, and I didn't have Worcestershire sauce, so I used A-1. I made this quickly on the skillet, toasted some slider buns, and had enough for 12 sliders for dinner over two days. Moist and tangy. The next time I make this, I think I may add a little more heat to my and my husband's portion by adding some red pepper flakes.

name: kittencal s chicken crescent roll casserole
review: This was good, but I didn't like how heavy and rich it was and I didn't even add all the cheese.  I had cheddar cheese soup instead of cream of chicken and omited the cheese that was to be added with the soup.  I too waited to put the soup on until the 10 or so minutes of baking.  I would play around with this recipe some more to make it lighter.<br/>UPDATE:  I added mixed veggies to the sauce and did not add cheese to the chicken filling.  We enjoyed these much more this time.

name: slow cooked bbq ribs  for crock pot
review: I did not have good luck with this recipe... I think quantities of salt and pepper would be helpful.  I agree that the sauce turned out to be very watered down.  My husband said to throw it away... but I hate to waste food.  I cut it into small strips, added more salt and pepper and undiluted barbecue sauce to save it... the the kids said they would eat it, but my husband still said it was too dry.  I do think it can also matter a lot the original meat... why is it so dry sometimes and other times not.

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: I made this for tonight's dinner. I actually started it the night before. I did the first five steps and put it in the fridge. When I got home from work tonight I cooked the pasta and put it in my large casserole dish,topped with the soup followed by the sauce and cheese and popped it in the oven. Easy.  DD wasn't sure if she liked it at first but we all agree, the more we ate, the more we liked it.

name: mrs  geraldine s ground beef casserole
review: Hubs really enjoyed the sweetness of the ground beef mixture and had 2 large servings for dinner...said he just couldn't resist.  I am sure i will be reminded to make this many times over.  Thanks!

name: tzatziki
review: Excellent. I used lemon juice in place of vinegar & added crumbled feta. Served on gyros with sliced yellow & red bell pepppers. Thanks for sharing!

name: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
review: Update 9/14/14 - Interesting, I just made these and realize that the recipe that's on the Quaker Oats box has changed. It calls for only 1/2c plus 6T of butter, and only 3/4 c brown sugar.  I was wondering why the cookies were turning out a lot lumpier than I remember.  I think this original recipe with more shortening and more brown sugar come out with a better texture.<br/><br/>These are my favorite OR cookies - they come out perfect every time.  I like my OR a little on the soft/chewy side, so I love the texture of these, and the taste cannot be beat - perfect amount of spice and raisins.

name: fantastic taco casserole
review: I have tried many taco casserole recipes, but this one was quite different from any I have tried. The refried bean layer is what makes it so incredibly delicious. Added a few sliced jalapenos on top. Perfect. Thanks for posting.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: One more 5-star review!  I've made many different dressings, but this is certainly the best balsamic vinaigrette I've ever had. Followed the instructions exactly, except for doubling the garlic (personal preference!). I can't see a reason to try any other. Thanks so much for posting! Made for Culinary Quest 2014.

name: quick butternut squash soup
review: For calories & fat I would give it 5-stars but I just didn't care much for this. I even roasted the squash thinking it would add some extra flavor. I am glad that it has been a huge success for others though! Maybe I am just not a big fan of butternut squash?!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: This recipe is worth the time it takes to make it.  Mine took 90 minutes, but I used 4 bananas, which could've been why. I added a 1/4 tsp of nutmeg as well.  AMAZING is what this is!! Thanks for the recipe :)

name: healthy no bake cookies
review: Delicious and easy! I have put them in the fridge to become a bit more chewy instead of soft as they were .. used part brown sugar. Thanks for this recipe

name: kittencal s best blasted rapid roast whole chicken
review: Without a doubt, best roast chicken I have ever made.  Winner winner - chicken dinner.  ;)

name: charlie s famous chicken salad with grapes
review: Great chicken salad.  Wasn't sure I would like the worchestershire but was good flavor.  A bit salty so may cut that a little. Served with potato sticks on top and apple crisp for dessert.  Great for a warm day.

name: awesome slow cooker pot roast
review: This version of slow cooker pot roast is the first I ever made way back in the day. Still good all these years later. Tender, well-seasoned, and the gravy is drinkable. Simply perfect. Thanks.

name: skillet parmesan chicken
review: Super simple and yummy. Thanks for sharing. Made for Culinary Quest 2014.

name: very moist banana nut bread
review: To make it a little healthier but still moist, I used about a half cup of applesauce and then topped off with oil to make the 3/4 cups. Because of using the applesauce, I cut the sugar back to 1 1/2 cups. It still was rather sweet though. I wish I had reduced it even more. The results were a moist, dense bread with plenty of banana flavor. I liked the use of pecans instead of the traditional walnuts. I used two 9x5-inch loaf pans. I wish I had used 8x5 as the loaves weren't as high as I like them.

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Made as directed using the 1 TB. honey.  When I tasted it, all I could taste was sweetness.  So I ended up adding a shake or 10 extra of ginger and garlic. It was entirely too sweet to have with steamed broccoli.  I had it again today dipping fried chicken strips and it seemed to have lost a bit of the sweetness.  I did not have a problem with obtaining the perfect texture nor was it gloopy after refrigeration. Will make again but will half the amount of sugar.  Thank you for the recipe.

name: panera bread  black bean soup
review: So this isn't identical to Panera's black bean soup, but it's still REALLY good.  Made it for football Sunday with some grilled sandwiches. It was the perfect meal for a fall day.  We'll be making this one again!

name: downunder cheese puffs
review: So EASY and delish! I added a dash of ground black pepper to the cheese mixture before baking. These Cheese Puffs were turned out great! Will totally make them again with other spices.

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: I made a half batch of these tonight and followed the recipe exactly--no changes needed.  They were absolutely perfect and will be going on my Christmas platters this year.

name: outback steakhouse style steak
review: Yummy. Probably the best rub I've ever made. Bet it would be better with the onion powder the recipe called for but I was out of it. Tried it with smoked paprika for 1 tsp of the regular. Just as good. Thanks.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: I prepared this for low carb and not low fat. It was very good and the sauce is like a sophisticated tartar/dill sauce. It was creamy and very good and easy. A keeper for sure. I omitted the cheddar cheese due to reviews and didnt miss it.

name: crock pot potato chowder
review: Quick and tasty!  I used low fat cream cheese.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: This is so simple to throw together.  I got everything going in the crock pot in the morning.  When I came home I added the cream cheese and cooked some brown rice.  I used homemade salsa and low fat cream cheese.  The family really enjoyed it.  I ate the leftover corn/bean/salsa sauce over the rice for lunch and that was just as yummy.

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: So delicious! I think I might pound the chicken a bit next time just for personal preference.

name: baja black beans  corn and rice
review: Easy, packed full of flavor, and a colorful side dish.

name: parmesan zucchini
review: Two pieces per person? Yeah, right. I just ate four! I love these. I cut diamonds in the zucchini and brushed with olive oil. Also added garlic powder. Served with pizza sauce. Thank you for a quick and delicious recipe.

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: Yum! I underbaked them some and that was a good decision--liked it a little fudgy! Great treat for a girls night out.

name: best banana bread
review: Yummy and Simple!  What else can you ask for?  The only thing I did different was add some chopped walnuts.  Thank you so much for sharing.

name: old fashioned banana cream pie
review: I followed the recipe carefully because I am a novice when it comes to making deserts.  My hopes soared when my mixture thickened almost instantly.  I thought, well, all the others that complained MUST have done something different.  It tasted really great, but my pie never set either.  Even after hours in the fridge.  So I just grabbed a spoon and enjoyed my banana pudding in a pie shell.  Thank you for the recipe.  I will make this again when I crave/need vanilla pudding.  The boxed version isn't available here so the recipe benefits me.

name: crock pot chicken  gravy and stuffing
review: LOVED it - a "hit" for all kiddos (ages 4 through 12!), and a "hit" for me, a full-time working mom, due to the ease of preparation. THIS is a keeper!!! Thanks for sharing!! So quick to throw together in the morning before work!

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: WOW! Our teenage son made this easy recipe (doubled it) on "his" night to make dinner. It was AMAZING! DEFINITELY a keeper! (Could be simplified/even quicker by buying frozen cubed potatoes if needed.) This is a weeknight "keeper!" Thanks for sharing!

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: This recipe is so easy to make your own!  I added a package of broccoli, cauliflower, and carrots to the mix.  Peas would be another nice addition. Instead of biscuits, I used croutons.  My DH loved it.

name: failproof french bread  bread machine
review: Turned out great.  Loved the flavor with a little butter and zucchini lasagna an chopped Italian salad.

name: oven roasted corn on the cob
review: This worked out very well. It is the only way I cook fresh corn on the cob.

name: pumpkin pie dip
review: I had a hard time telling whether I should get canned pumpkin or canned pumpkin pie mix. After checking through the reviews, I noticed that the people who used pumpkin pie mix typically said that the dip was too sweet, so I chose to try it with the canned pumpkin. I think that was the correct choice, as the flavor was wonderful and everyone adored it! Delicious-this was the hit of the office potluck with ginger snaps and graham crackers (some people even added whipped cream on top to make mini pumpkin pies). Yum!

name: shredded chicken for enchiladas  tostadas  tacos
review: This was awesome and super simple. I used canned, diced tomatoes with green chilies in them (which I drained most of the liquid from) but otherwise followed the directions as written. Really, really great. Will make again.

name: corned beef in beer  crock pot
review: This was delicious and came out perfectly. It took 9 hours, during which I fretted while it appeared to dry completely out and then magically shred and become melt-in-your mouth tender. Used a whole 12 oz. bottle of Shiner Bock and added a diced parsnip to the roast. This will be my go-to corned beef recipe.

name: fabulous beef stew
review: This stew is so delicious and just perfect for the cool fall weather! Thanks!

name: green beans with cherry tomatoes
review: I found these really really good, due to a no salt diet in one guest, i used garlic powder instead of salt and i had to substitute thyme for basil

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: AWESOME! I made as directed except I added 1 t. garlic powder & 1-2 t. of dill weed. I used an immersion blender to make it creamy & smooth. Thanks for posting...it is a keeper!

name: marvelous broccoli salad
review: I went looking for this in my reviews and it wasn't there.  I could have sworn I had reviewed it.  This is FANTASTIC.  Quite simple.  I'm not sure how long it would actually last, because I make up a double batch (for just me), and in two days, it is gone.

name: potsie s creamed chicken and biscuits casserole
review: Really great casserole! I used sour cream instead of mayo. I used that new cream of chicken with mushrooms soup. I added 1.5 cups of heated frozen peas. I baked 15 minutes then put the cheese and biscuits and more cheese on top. Mine needed another 25 minutes before the biscuits were golden. I agree there is much more biscuit than casserole so I would probably use more chicken and/or veggies next time. I used all the meat from one store-bought rotisserie chicken and I don't think it was enough. Buying two would make for an expensive casserole so I'd probably just cook my own next time. But all that aside, it tasted great and everyone loved it, and I would definitely make it again!

name: tsr version of ihop buttermilk pancakes by todd wilbur
review: Light and fluffy and just perfect!

name: my no roll pie crust
review: If not for all the great reviews, I would have been skeptical that something so simple could actually work, but it did! It really did! And it was really, really good, even. As a bottom crust, it's super simple. Like some others, I also tried to use it on the top, starting with the ball and pressing it with my hands into a flat shape. It was difficult to transfer, but it worked. For sure, though, as a bottom crust, as this seems to be intended, it is really perfect! Thank you so much for sharing.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Incredibly good! I didn't have any left over chicken, so I butterflied a couple of large chicken breasts, rubbed them with olive oil and salt and pepper and baked them at 350F/175C for 40 minutes and let them cool before chopping them up. I did a top and bottom crust, but next time I'll only do a top crust as I think the recipe indicates (but even then, only one). I added just a bit of frozen mixed veggies to give it a little more color inside. I think this recipe is really versatile once you have that delicious base. It was a huge hit! Thanks so much for sharing it!

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: I really enjoyed these! I just wanted to keep eating them! A great way to use rotisserie chicken.

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: tasted like eggs. not going to make again.

name: crabs   garlic butter baked crab legs
review: Made as written. Delicious.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: I didn't mind this, neither did my husband, but its probably not something I would make again or add to our regular rotation. The main reason being the kids weren't fans. As I always say, it was worth a try!

name: creamy cajun chicken pasta
review: A very tasty pasta dish. I agree with other reviewers, it's like alfredo, but with a kick! The sun-dried tomatoes add extra tang and flavour to each mouthful. I saved the leftovers and took them to work the next day. One thing I learned with cream based pasta dishes, and any pasta really, is it is better if you store and reheat the pasta and the sauce separately. If you don't, the pasta soaks up most of the sauce and the pasta is gluggy but the sauce is either dry or separated!

name: crock pot whole chicken
review: A nice way to cook a whole chicken. Tender and flavourful. I still prefer the oven for a whole chicken though.

name: meatball sub casserole
review: I have made this twice, once following the recipe as directed but the second time I toasted the bread a little bit first and we prefer it that way so the bread isn't quite as soggy.  Next time I will also increase the meatballs to use 1 1/2 lbs. of hamburger as we didn't think there were enough meatballs.

name: puppy chow or monkey munch
review: Made this with white chocolate instead. Wow, good!

name: slow cooker chicken noodle soup
review: 4 stars only because it is too salty. Definitely switch off the slow cooker before you put in the noodles.

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Cooked an extra 30 minutes trying to caramelize the liquid.  It never thickened.  Instead I served the thin liquid over brown rice with stir fry veggies.  Great combo.  The kids gave it 5 stars, but I gave it 4 because of the liquid difficulty.  We will make this again.

name: chewy granola bars
review: Sooooo good!!!  This was the first time I've ever had a 2nd grader ask me for a recipe.  Ha!  This was delicious and held together very well.  Thanks much!

name: simple baked chicken drumsticks
review: Easy and delicious.  Thanks for posting.

name: banana banana bread
review: AMAZING!  MOIST!  DELICIOUS!  I used coconut oil in place of butter and I added some mini chocolate chips.  Wonderful!

name: intensely chocolate cocoa brownies
review: Love these brownies!  Thanks for posting.

name: halloween party treat  candy corn and peanut mix
review: PayDay, PayDay, PayDay!!!!

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: Oh My! We loved this because we loved the sauce. I do believe you must love the sauce for this to be a 5 star recipe to you. After going through all the reviews, I started to saute the onions or make some additions- Glad I didn't, you don't need to. If you "finely" chop the onions as stated, they work fine. If you cover the "top and sides" of your meatloaf with the sauce as stated, you don't need to add any spices to your meatloaf because the sauce is the maker of this meatloaf. Again- We Loved It!!! Thank you Nita!!!

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: I love this recipe just the way it is posted. I put in three thawed chicken breasts with the other ingredients on top. I cooked into on low for six hours. When I went to add the cream cheese, the toppings were a little dry. I added about 1/2 cup of water and then the cream cheese. Next time, I will add a can of diced tomatoes to give some more liquid. I also didn't shredded my chicken bfeasts. I served it on top of garlic butter spiral noodles. A great combination of favors.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Followed the recipe exactly and LOVED it.  A little different, in a good way; from the usual red or green enchiladas and couldn't have been any easier.  A mild, creamy sauce set the chicken of so well.  I think next time I might even add some cilantro and jalapenos just for a little kick to see how that works, but it's perfect just the way it is.  Had a lot left over (there's only two of us) and have frozen the rest for another meal, will be anxious to see how that works out

name: sticken chicken
review: This is not good at all. Too sweet sauce. For 3 hours of cooking, I want something that taste good.

name: olive garden copycat zuppa toscana
review: A family favorite. I used hot Italian sausage instead of mild. Love this soup. Husband loves this soup. Did potatoes unpeeled and used chicken base and more garlic. YUM

name: the only chocolate cake recipe you ll ever need   devil s food
review: Great recipe.  Thanks for posting.

name: the best chicken tortilla soup
review: This is a good soup for a cold day.  While we all liked it, no one felt it was "The Best"  Chicken Tortilla soup we have had.  May combine this with others we have tried and tweak it to our families personal taste.

name: bakery style chewy chocolate chip cookies
review: These turned out really nice. I baked them on a silpat on cookie sheets. Took a little longer to brown up, but were crisp on the edges and chewy in the center. I just realized the butter was to have been melted & I used 2 whole eggs which yielded 31 nice sized cookies. I have been making cookie dough in the food processor since I discovered how easy it is & how quickly it comes together (try it, you won't regret it). I omitted the nuts since the kids prefer  them without nuts. Thanks for sharing!

name: chicken curry in a hurry
review: Like jentastic, I didn't have any raisins on hand, so I had to leave them out. Nor did I have yogurt, so once again I followed jentastics review and used sour cream instead. I served it over rice.  DH and I were the only ones who liked this. Guess my crew just isn't fans of Indian food.

name: simply sour cream chicken enchiladas
review: Made this for dinner. Super creamy. I used home canned chicken as it is what I have. I Carmelized the onions in butter then added a little cumin and taco seasoning to the onions then added the meat after draining. I let this warm through. Then I stirred in some leftover rice.<br/>We were having the missionaries for dinner, plus we expecting a friend as well. Cooking for 12 people, this was fabulous! Served it with salad and pie for dessert of course. <br/><br/>Oh, I also puréed the peppers before adding to the sauce so I wouldn't hear complaints of grossness.. Even my picky eaters scarfed this down and had seconds! This was requested to be added to the monthly plan! Hurrah!

name: ginger me up chicken  low fat honey   ginger chicken breasts
review: Rock solid recipe!  My DH was licking the casserole dish for all that lovely sauce!    I love recipes that are so easy peasy!!!  Kudos on a great find!!!

name: cinnamon raisin bread for the bread machine
review: Yum!! I've made other breads before but this was my very first raisin bread and it was definitely a success! I did add wheat gluten to my flour (about a rounded teaspoon per cup of flour) which helped the bread have a nice rise. I also followed other suggestions and soaked my raisins first in some hot water (I personally found 3/4 cup was a good amount of raisins but will probably throw in an extra handful or two next time just because I love raisins!) Then I let the same water cool a bit and used that for the water in the recipe. I also added the raisins directly into the liquids before adding the dry ingredients and my bread machine had no issues mixing the raisins into the dough (and my raisins stayed intact through the process!) I also used brown sugar instead of regular white sugar, cut the salt down to 1/2 teaspoon (as I used salted butter) used 2 teaspoons of cinnamon and left everything else the same. Usually I will cut my dough in half and bake them as 2 loaves, but this time I decided to just have one big loaf and ended up with a REALLY big, really fluffy and really tasty loaf of raisin bread! I baked the loaf at 350 for about 40 minutes in the oven. I can't wait to have it for breakfast tomorrow!! Thank you!

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: While this is good (and rich too) I like my recipe better.  Mine has more flavorings and less fat.  It is not posted here but includes a bay leaf, paprika, onion, and regular milk instead of cream and milk.  I think the raw flour taste in this is a reasonable critique.  I felt this did have some raw notes.  I'm not sure if it is because I didn't simmer the sauce long enough or if the roux was the problem.  I did cook the flour in the butter a bit more than the usual amount for a white sauce, but maybe it was not long enough.  So, be sure to cook the flour in the butter a long time (longer than usual).   I also used panko bread crumbs, which I think was a mistake.  Regular bread crumbs would have been better in my opinion - just goes to show you that the recipe means what it says.  The panko texture was just too crispy and distracted from the gooey goodness of the macaroni although the taste was unaffected.

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: The boys in the house thought it was "fine" but my 7 year old daughter and I really liked this.  I discovered too late that I only had one pound of cooked ground beef in the freezer, so I only had half of the meat.  So I put in an extra 1/3 cup of noodles.  I also put in about 2 cups of celery and 1.5 cups of carrots.  Therefore it probably was thicker than intended.  But I liked that about it :). Used frozen peas instead of split peas.  I almost tossed corn in there but refrained.

name: basil pesto
review: I had a bunch of basil from my garden, so I buzzed this up and froze them in ice cube trays for future use.  Tastes great.

name: parmesan sage pork chops
review: If salt and fat are wrong, parmesan sage pork chop doesn't want to be right. Fabulous!

name: spinach salad with honey bacon dressing
review: Whole family really enjoyed this!  Only thing I'll say is it makes waaaay too much dressing.  You can easily cut it in half.  Otherwise, pretty much perfect.  Thanks for the great recipe Hey Jude.....

name: best banana bread
review: Love it...added finely chopped walnuts...loved it even more.  Thank you!

name: puppy chow or monkey munch
review: I have made puppy chow dozens of times and am always trying new recipes. I liked this one but I think I like it better without the butter and vanilla. It has a more intense flavor and I think I eat less. I also use Crispix instead of Chex most often because it is what we have on hand.

name: beef roast
review: This wasn't for us.  It just tasted like the gravy.

name: roasted parmesan garlic cauliflower
review: My family isn't a huge fan of cauliflower, but everyone seemed to like this. Of course I added extra garlic, which is a must for my family of garlic lovers.  DD said it could even use some more!  This was really easy to throw together and a great way to use up that head of cauliflower in the fridge.

name: pork tenderloin  the best ever
review: Happy to be review #100 for this great recipe.  My husband wanted to cook the pork on the grill but I really wanted to try this recipe.  So hoping that it would turn out ok.  Made exactly as written.  Delicious comfort food.  We had it with mashed potatoes and broccoli.  I froze the second loin and gravy which I reheated last night and had with egg noodles and green beans. Again delicious.  As my husband finished the last of the leftovers for lunch today he said " you can make this again whenever you want!" I will and soon!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: If you live in rural area you don't always have luxury of all ingredients I only used a 2 lb pork roast butt so I had to adjust the times. 8 hours probably would have worked perfectly but I unfortunatly plugged in the wrong appliance and did not notice for a few hours so I had to cook on high for 2 1/2 hours then turn low and cook for 2 1/2 hours more. I shredded then added barbecue sauce and cooked for an additonal 2 hours. then warm as had to keep warm until my party. I had 8 sandwiches plus extra in a bowl plus all men ate 2 sandwiches apeace plus they added extra meat to their sanwiches. Everyone loved the sandwiches. I probably could have rated higher but with all my problems one of which I eat very little meat - which was no fault of recipe I rate 4. I used recipe#19023 for barbecue sauce and this time it came out kinda strong so used vinegar/sugar trick to lessen spices work with some but not all types over spicing I used half vinegar half sugar. As some of the reviews said it needed more liquid even though I halved recipe I used the full amount of ginger ale. or rather the substitute one of the members suggested 1-1/2 c water, 1 T brown sugar though I only used only 1 T. ginger root grated. this is a fantastic recipe

name: pete s scratch pancakes
review: Excellent! Very fluffy and light. The only change I made was to use dried buttermilk and water for the milk.

name: brussels sprouts in garlic butter
review: Tasted great! I used minced garlic at the end and did not have any parm on hand. Thanks!

name: world s best chocolate chip cookies
review: I was skeptical, but yes these may be the world's best chocolate chip cookies. This recipe doubles well--I often bake half and freeze half of the cookie balls so that I can pop them in the oven for fresh baked cookies anytime! This works as long as my husband doesn't go on a frozen cookie dough raid.

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: This was a nice change of pace and satisfying on a cool fall evening.  Thank you for sharing this recipes.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: I have to admit that I decided to make this recipe on the spur of the moment (at the supermarket) and, having to reconstruct it in my head, grabbed a container of half-and-half rather than heavy cream.  Other than that, I followed the rest of the recipe to a "T" (3 cups tomato juice, 1 cup vegetable broth in my case) and it was delicious!  I don't think it needs the lemon juice -- it was acidic enough (although perhaps the heavy cream would have made a difference).  Perfect served with sandwiches on a snowy winter's day, and *so* easy!

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: These were tasty, DH ate three with his stew!  The 15 balls was right on, filled the dish perfectly!  Thanks.

name: greek potatoes  oven roasted and delicious
review: These are very good and super easy. I cut the recipe in half and it still turned out quite yummy.  Thank you for sharing!

name: frijoles negros  cuban black beans
review: I made a half batch of this to go with some vieja ropa and white rice. I didn't have a green pepper since I used it in the vieja ropa, but it was still delicious. <br/>3 of my 5 children gobbled it up (the other two tend toward extreme pickiness so that wasn't a surprise) and my husband and I both enjoyed it very much.<br/>The nicest part is how easy it is to make!

name: poverty meal
review: I hate the name, but love the recipe. Thank you for sharing this simple and satisfying recipe.

name: lentil soup for people who thought they hated lentils    meat op
review: oh, This is my NEW favorite soup!  I have made this once, with brown lentils...all I had on hand...running to store today, to get red lentils...I would have NEVER thought I loved Lentils!  So glad I tried this!  Yum......

name: yes  virginia there is a great meatloaf
review: This was a good first meatloaf for me. I too added 1 tbs Worcestershire as a replacement for 1tbs of the vinegar in the sauce. I also added a couple of garlic cloves and sauted with the onions before adding to the meat mixture and added a teaspoon of all purpose seasoning. It came out very tasty.

name: fannie farmer s classic baked macaroni   cheese
review: This was a great comfort food.  I used Cabot Extra Sharp Cheddar, and used skim milk and half & half with no ill effects.  Leftovers reheated beautifully.  8 y.o. DS absolutely loved it.  Thanks for sharing.<br/><br/>Updated 11/2104 to add:  I don't know why I even bother trying other mac & cheese recipes; they always leave me disappointed, and I eventually find my way back here.  In a hurry, I used a pre-grated "artisan" cheddar blend from Sargento.  It was just as good as with the Cabot.

name: leftover mashed potato pancakes
review: Wonderful potato recipe. Quick and easy.  Thanks for posting.

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Moist, tender and full of banana flavor and not too sweet.  Quick and easy to put together with simple ingredients.  I used 4 black bananas, sub 1 cup whole wheat flour, no nuts - allergies, used 1/2 cup chocolate chips because it's chocolate!  Sprinkled top with turbinado sugar for the crystallized look.  Baked 27 minutes,  12 fluffy beautiful brown muffins came out.  Thank you.

name: family favorite oatmeal pancakes
review: Wonderful recipe! Perfect fall/winter breakfast food. I added 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and used a gluten-free flour blend. I also used unsweetened vanilla almond milk to keep them dairy-free. They came out amazing and I will definitely make them again!

name: bestest hamburger soup
review: Used 1/2 meat, omitted peas, added one green pepper and one jalepeno.  No cheese needed.

name: edna s apple crumble  aka  apple crisp
review: Absolutely delicious crumble! I did, however, make a few changes the second time around.<br/>I reduced the brown sugar by 2 tbsp. Reduced the nutmeg to 1/4 tsp because it was wayyy too overpowering. And cut up some extra butter and sprinkled randomly on top of the crisp before baking. <br/>Thank you for the amazing recipe. I made the changes due to personal preference only.

name: kittencal s bakery buttercream  frosting icing
review: Excellent

name: tasty buns
review: OH My, Oh My, these buns are so delicious, so easy, I let the dough rise twice, then made the buns. So fast, So light and tasty. They remind me of rolls my mom use to make. I have made them twice. The first time I made them I added some cardamom, candied fruit and dried cramberries to part of the dough, delicious. This recipe is definitely a keeper. Thank you so much for sharing.<br/>Update: I have made these SOOOOOooo many times everyone loves them. I am always asked to make these buns for dinners. Recently I made them for a dinner & our new Granddaughter-in-law was surprised that these were homemade. She said, you made these from scratch. I gave her the recipe.I am making them for Thanksgiving dinner at our DS& DDIL's.  Update Nov 2014 I will be making these again this year as I have for 8 years. So good & easy. I am always asked to bring the Tasty Buns & My Pumpkin Pie.

name: white chili   football soup
review: Excellent.  Only used one can of beans.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: This recipe didn't work out too well for me. The brussels turned out dry on the outside and mushy inside. I think they should have come out 10 or 15 mins. sooner, but then they may have lost the roasted flavor. These just weren't for us. Thanks for posting the recipe. It's always fun trying new things.

name: enchilada sauce
review: This was the first time ever for me making my own Enchilada sauce and I definitely will again! This went down a storm! It was quick to make and made plenty for my enchilada recipe - I like things a little milder, but that's just personal preferene, so for me I'd take out a little chilli, but my partner loved the heat and coudn't stop raving about dinner!

name: weight watchers parmesan chicken cutlets
review: I couldn't believe how easy this recipe was! And it tasted great! I love recipes where they don't taste "skinny" as I love my food! The seasoning was perfect and there was enough cheese to taste, but not make you feel like you've over indulged! I'll definitely make these again.

name: cranberry orange muffins
review: I must add a 5 star review to all the other 5 star reviews that this recipe has received.  I made loaves instead of muffins but it did not change the deliciousness nor texture.  Great balance of flavors, not difficult to make at all.  Thanks for posting, I will use this recipe again!!

name: homemade chicken pot pie
review: Wow!  We really loved this quick and easy pot pie!  The convenience of using frozen vegetables and refrigerated pie crust really cut down the prep time.  I made this in a 9x13" baking dish and only used (1) package of the pie crusts.  After cutting the bottom and top crusts to fit the pan, I used the removed bits to fill in the open areas of the crust.  It may not have been pretty, but it worked out fine.  Also, I baked it for about 50 minutes to make sure that the bottom crust was done.  This made great leftovers for lunch the following day, too. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper!  **Made for 2014 Football Pool**

name: country white bread or dinner rolls  bread machine
review: Since I have been watching my carbs, i haven't had bread in few months. Being Thanksgiving, I decided to not really worry about carbs and have a little "cheat day" (but did use Splenda in place of sugar).  This bread = completely worth it!  Thank you!

name: cracker barrel green beans
review: I love green beans...and I LOVE this recipe!  I'm watching my carbs right now, so i added Splenda instead of sugar - still love it!

name: kittencal s easy no fail make anytime turkey gravy
review: Absolutely terrific. We halfed the recipe as we only had that amount of turkey drippings but it was fab. Smooth, creamy, tasty gravy. The roux and the whisking makes it great.  We used recipe #77861 for roast turkey and the drippings from that flavored the gravy nicely. Everyone loved it. It was poured on everything. Of course it was gone in a flash. Will be the go to gravy recipe from now on. Thanks for posting Kittencal. Enjoy! ChefDLH

name: kim s sweet potato casserole
review: Thought we'd try a different recipe for sweet potato casserole this year. This was great! Not sure it was better, but a little bit different. I liked the addition of marshmallows on top. Thanks!

name: best ever pumpkin pie
review: This is a delicious pumpkin pie! I added extra cinnamon to taste. My daughter and I loved it!

name: buttery farm biscuits
review: We really enjoyed these delicious biscuits.  They were so quick and easy to make, using ingredients always found in the pantry and they taste better than any you buy  in the stores.   They were perfection.  The biscuits were big, they had  a crunchy top and bottom crust and a tender filling. They were awesome served warm with berry jam but also just as wonderful served with homemade baked beans and Maple Peameal Bacon Roast. Thanks for sharing  a recipe I will make often.

name: ww 0 point weight watchers cabbage soup
review: I prefer a variation of the WW soup (Recipe #278655). Thus the 4 stars.

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: Mmmmm.....delicious! Thanks for sharing the recipe!

name: treebeard s red beans  and rice
review: 11/2008 AMAZING! I have been on a quest to find an easy & yummy RBR recipe. I will stop here.<br/>I halved the recipe using (2) 15oz cans of red kidney beans- rinsed, 2 cups water, 14 oz. smoked turkey sausage,  all the other specified ingredient  amounts (less salt),  then let it simmer away for a few hours to desired consistency. YUM! Thanks PanNan! 12/2014 We can't get enough of this. My 1streview made no sense so I edited it. Love this dish

name: wet burritos
review: Best I've ever made!  Thanks

name: soft snickerdoodle cookies
review: These turned out beautiful, prepped in the food processor. We were, however disappointed as they were missing something, lacked flavor. I feel as though they would be improved with the addition of vanilla extract. Thanks for sharing.

name: thai coconut rice
review: I had trouble with the method so I didn't want to leave a star rating. I used basmatic rice and ended up with a creamy mush which tasted great but was not what I was looking for. I think my rice was to blame as it was a brand I hadn't used before but I also didn't like the final colour of the rice with the turmeric and ginger, it was a bit yellowy and looked like a pilaf rather than the very white fluffy Thai rice that I am used to in restaurants. I think it would be a great recipe to have when you are in a hurry and want to make something a little different.

name: olive garden style chicken and gnocchi soup
review: Wonderful!  This will definitely be added to our rotation.  I made just as directed.

name: mom s chocolate cupcakes
review: I made these cupcakes twice over the weekend.  I was told that they were the best cupcakes I've ever made.  I'm not sure if that means that all of the rest of the cupcakes I've made (and I've made plenty) have been bad, or that these are really great.  I'm assuming the latter.  :)  I was told that they are very moist and chocolaty.  They're easily put together and economical too (no butter).  I topped them with a chocolate ganache.  Thank you for posting this recipe.  It'll be made again (not again this weekend though... :) ),

name: alton brown s baked brown rice
review: Great way to do brown rice.  Used in veggie burgers.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: So easy and tastes great!  I had a 4 pound shoulder.  I only had 10 hours overnight, so I did 2.5 hours on high, then 7.5 on low.  Came out great!  My son doesn't care for heavy BBQ sauce, so I mixed it 1:1 with the cooking liquid to add before the second cooking phase, and served with more sauce on the side.  A little salt and pepper, and it was great!  Can wait to try freezing some.

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: oh my GOSH!  This was easy, simple to make, with few ingredients...but with AWESOME flavor!,  I have never been able to get my DH to try potato soup, he just does not like it....my son kept going on and on about it and my DH gave it a try...guess what....He loves THIS Potato Soup!  I followed directions to the T, except:  Used Swanson's Chicken broth, 2 cans - 3.5 C, Regular Salt and black pepper.Thank you Parsley for a outstanding Recipe!

name: uncle bill s green split pea with hambone soup
review: Wow, I can't believe I have not rated this. We have enjoyed this for years!  Thank you Uncle Bill!  Awesome Soup!

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: Fantastic recipe! I used more than 3 pounds of legs and there was still plenty of sauce. I cut the honey back to 1/2 cup and used gluten-free tamari sauce. I baked the legs for 30 minutes, then turned them over. Baked another 30 minutes while basting frequently. This is a fool-proof recipe good enough for company!

name: ultimate pizza sauce
review: Very good.  Very easy.  makes lots.  I quadrupled it and I think I have enough sauce for about 12-15 pizzas.  But I'm not complaining.  Yummy.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Easy and savory way to make Brussels sprouts. Makes the kitchen smell great. I made half the amount and would recommend a cooler oven of 325, since the amount I roasted started burning after 15 minutes at 400. Thank you for sharing.

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I have been making this recipe for a couple of years.......love it. When I ran across it today, I realized that I had not reviewed it.  I agree, a bit of liquid smoke ups the flavor a lot, but then it depends on which BBQ sauce is used. <br/>Just a terrific recipe and I use it very often. <br/><br/>I should add that the only reason I might add liquid smoke is because I have yet to find a BBQ sauce that has that flavor that I'm looking for. So if the taste isn't in the sauce, why not add something to give it the flavor I like.  Donna

name: easy crock pot moroccan chicken  chickpea and apricot tagine
review: This was very good. I used rabbit stew meat, no cayenne pepper. I didn't have any apricots; thought about raisins but didn't. Will try apricots another time.

name: low carb pizza
review: Very good pizza. The crust held up very nicely, but was a little "eggy," which is to be expected. Don't worry if you have little clumps of cream cheese in your egg mixture. It all bakes up just fine.  I would recommend this pizza if you are on a gluten-free or low-carb diet!

name: southern fried salmon patties
review: A bit bland

name: cheese tortellini pesto pasta salad
review: Great recipe for a party or gathering- it is easy to put together, doesn't need to marinate for hours before serving, makes plenty and tastes good too! My family really liked this recipe. We will be making this one again!

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: Turned out great so moist and nice.

name: famous challah
review: Wow....you made us look pro. Wonderful recipe and instructions. Thanks for posting!

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: This recipe is wonderful!  I followed KristieKatz's review and doubled the sauce and put it all in the crockpot for 4 hours on low.

name: gingerbread  for cookies or a  gingerbread house
review: Excellent! This was a great dough & required minimal effort with perfect results. I only use real butter when baking,it's imperative. I substituted 1c whole wheat flour for the AP flour. Glazed with a lemon glaze (1/4 c. Softened butter, 1/4 c. Lemon juice & 1 1/4 c. Powdered sugar) & frosted cookies warm from the oven. Thanks, we're using this one going forward!

name: 100  whole grain wheat bread
review: Very nice bread. I only had 2 packets of dry yeast which is a little less than the 2 Tablespoons called for, but the bread still turned out great!

name: caramelized butternut squash
review: Yummm!  Fast & easy.  Nothing to be tending at the last minute.  Ingredients I have readily available.  Healthy and delicious!  What a great recipe.  Thank you so much.

name: sugar cookie icing
review: I used this recipe to frost some Christmas cookies today.  The icing had a nice glossy appearance and looks nice on the cookies.  I did have to add an extra amount of corn syrup in order to make it spreadable.  Thank you for posting this recipe!

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: These were delicious!! I made them with a lemon cake mix and DH and I both loved them. Thanks Karen!!

name: easy peezy pizza dough  bread machine pizza dough
review: Excellent pizza dough and so easy.  I have made this several times and it always turns out great.  I do cut back on the sugar to 2 tsp as a personal preference and on occasion I added some Italian seasoning for a change, but as written is just wonderful.

name: overnight french toast casserole
review: Very yummy! It was sweet. I halved the recipe and cut the sugar down some, but may cut it by half next time. I used left over challah bread and it worked great. I loved how simple this recipe was and it was so nice to wake to breakfast nearly being done. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: I personally liked it. But my hubby and kids won't eat it.

name: christmas rum balls or bourbon balls
review: I have been wanting to make these for years and haven't gotten to them....until this year.  BIG MISTAKE waiting all those years.  This little gem is awesome.  I added them to our holiday trays, but put them in little bags writing on them 'adults only".  Everyone loves them.  Thank you for sharing this yummy treat.

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: I used Betty Crocker Triple Chocolate Fudge because I don't like Devil's Food.  They taste just like brownies.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: yum

name: to die for make ahead mashed potatoes
review: These are really tasty. But, I have to say a little too rich for us. We thought it was almost like a potato cheesecake. Both DH and I want to make them again but use about 1/4 of the cream cheese and add some milk. Loved the other mix-ins and the ease of the recipe. Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Way too watery (Yes I DO know how to use cornstarch in fact I prefer clear jel!) and lacking in flavor.  I revamped the entire recipe, increased the amount of soy sauce, reduced the amount of water, used FRESH ginger and FRESH garlic and added more honey and sugar, along with some toasted sesame seeds and then it was edible.,

name: granny s banana cream pie
review: Great recipe!  I used gram cracker crust, an extra banana and a little more vanilla and the pie was fantastic.  I am confident that when made as written the pie would be just as good.  I made it for a dinner party and got rave reviews.  Thank you for sharing.

name: incredibly delicious cheese garlic bread spread
review: Updating my previous review -<br/>    5-stars instead of my original 2 stars.  I think it must be the quality of the ingredients I used this time compared to the first time I made this. I started with a loaf of fresh, homemade Italian bread.  I used unsalted butter instead of margarine.  The cheddar cheese I used was labelled 'Seriously Sharp White Cheddar'.  <br/><br/>With nearly 200 5 star ratings, I feel weird giving it 2 stars but for me it was just fair.  The cheddar cheese seemed out of place on garlic bread. I couldn't really taste the garlic or the parmesan cheese. I did like how baking, rather than broiling, the bread resulted in a crispy top and bottom.

name: mashed sweet potatoes
review: Was surprised that the recipe didn't call for the potatoes to be cooked first. But it was delicious.

name: ro tel chicken spaghetti
review: this is really good.  Its simple to prepare and when you mix it all up after cooking its nice and creamy.  My family really liked this.  thanks for sharing.

name: ramen noodle egg foo yung
review: I liked it but no one else in the family does :(

name: kittencal s greek moussaka
review: added sliced parboiled potatoes on base then the eggplant, minced lamb tomato sauce,eggplant,bechamel sauce......very very very good!!

name: panera s cream cheese potato soup
review: Really good!  This is the easiest potato soup I've ever made!  (Made just as written.)  Thanks.

name: meatball sub casserole
review: We loved this! All the flavours from one of my favourite sandwiches in a casserole, which made it OK to eat for dinner! I love homemade meatballs and with the sauce and bread base as well it was delicious. Even though the bread was a little soggy, we didn't mind at all. I followed the recipe exactly and would make this again.

name: low   slow oven baked ribs   super simple
review: These oven baked ribs were really delicious.  Although they do fall off the bone, they are tender and moist and your fingers stay clean since you can use your fork : )  This recipe is so easy and I liked the idea that I could just leave them in the oven and they required very little attention until the end.  Served these delicious ribs for my New Year's dinner along with my Southern blackeyed peas, cabbage, potato salad and cornbread.

name: awesome baked pork chops
review: I cannot believe I haven't posted a review of this amazing recipe before - I've made this at least a dozen times.  Of all the ways I prepare pork chops this is my DH and my favorite.  Very easy to pull together and the chops are amazingly tender - the sauce is very good over rice or noodles.  Thanks so much for posting Yooper:)

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: This was definitely easy because I didn't have to chop garlic or ginger or wait for the beef to marinate.  Since I am vegan I used substitute "beef tips" instead of real meat.  Also, I didn't have enough broccoli so I added a chopped green squash along with the broccoli I had.  We both finished up a half recipe in one sitting.

name: the best ever waffles
review: The butter content is too high for the ratio of dry ingredients making for a very thin batter and a rubbery waffle. I think if you halve the amount of butter (and even replace with canola oil), it would probably be an outstanding waffle. The flavor was good, just the texture wasn't what we'd hoped it'd be.

name: thick and creamy new england clam chowder
review: This is a great recipe--and while I usually don't like using canned soup, I am glad I tried this! I did make a couple of changes based on other reviews: I did not add the bacon (I didn't miss it at all) and used a couple Tbs of butter instead. I also used 1 10 oz can of baby clams, 1 6.5 oz can of chopped clams, and 1 6.5 oz can of minced clams. I cut back to two Russet potatoes (plenty!), minced two ribs of celery that I cooked with the onion, and then used cream of potato soup. I also added some parsley, subbed some thyme for the dill, and added 1/2 Tbs of sherry. It tasted great and I will definitely make this again!

name: best banana bread
review: Made just as directed, and it was amazing.  Definitely will be my go-to banana bread now!

name: cottage cheese roast  vegetarian meatloaf
review: My husband and I did not care for this meatloaf. It seem to lack flavor, and it didn't even come close to tasting like a meatloaf.! We ended up topping our slices with Sweet Baby Ray's Sweet 'n Spicy Barbecue Sauce, which was the only thing that gave this meatloaf flavor. We did eat 2 slices, but ended up throwing out the rest. Guess we much prefer our meatloaf made with real beef.

name: 24k carrots
review: Really good. Super fast and easy to fix. Thanks for the recipe!

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: I've made this twice without substitutions. The first time I made it I used the Sweet Baby Ray Barbecue Sauce and found it just a bit bland. But then the second time I made it with Jack Daniels Barbecue Sauce, and it was fantastic. I'm giving it five stars because the recipe calls for "favorite barbecue sauce" rather than a specific brand, so allows for "each to one's own taste"! Also, the second time I had to use what was labelled a 4-lb center-cut port roast; I'm assuming this means it's a shoulder cut but I'm not sure. Anyway I slow-cooked it on low 9 hours before adding the barbecue sauce, and it came out falling apart tender and easy to pull apart. I then cooked it another hour and was all set.

name: finger lickin good bbq sauce
review: Made this sauce tonight for chicken and fell in love!  I did add a pinch of salt and had to use garlic powder and dehydrated onions.  I can only imagine the taste with fresh onions and garlic!  Thanks.

name: copycat  green giant niblets corn in butter sauce
review: The corn was so delicious prepared this way.  It was sweet and tender surrounded in a lovely, silky butter sauce.  It was perfect served over saffron rice.  Thank you for sharing a recipe that I will make again.  Made for What's on the Menu Tag Game 2015.

name: la madeleine s tomato basil soup
review: Wow....delicious! So few ingredients, so little time and so tasty.  Winner! I used evaporated milk instead of cream and half the butter called for . Total keeper recipe! Thanks for sharing the recipe.

name: easy lemon pound cake
review: Delightfully moist and light and very lemony.

name: milk free  egg free pancakes
review: We were out of milk and my kids wanted pancakes. These were really great! We used the egg in the recipe. Will make again, even if I do have milk in the house. Thanks!

name: roasted cauliflower   16 roasted cloves of garlic
review: Such an easy-fix & no sml wonder that your recipe has a nearly perfect rating after so many reviews. It quite simply deserves every single star it has gotten & then some. I made it exactly as written, but reduced the temp & cooked it a bit longer than stated. Then I turned off the oven & let it sit there while I finished the rest of our meal. It only got better! I love this recipe! Thx for sharing it w/us. :-)

name: pork chops yum yum
review: Been wanting to try this for quite some time & was VERY disappointed. The sauce was terrible!!! Won't be making this again...sorry!!!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: Excellent!  I did what other reviewers did and cooked for 15 minutes then draining the fat/juice prior to adding the sauce. Also, for the sauce, I subbed 2T of BBQ sauce for the ketchup and added more minced garlic. I lined my pan with tin foil for easy clean-up. There was an abundance of sauce, so I only poured about 1/2 on the wings, I will save the rest for something else. Thanks for posting!

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: Loved how easy and such good flavors.

name: traditional irish shepherd s pie
review: Yummy! I froze leftover mashed potatoes with this in mind and am glad I did. Made it exactly as written except with canned vs. frozen peas because I could buy a smaller amount of them (didn't want any left over since DH doesn't really like them.)  I used ketchup instead of paste. Might have overcooked as the gravy wasn't as plentiful as I'd like (Suns game went into double OT!). Don't overcook!

name: simple baked chicken drumsticks
review: So simple, so delicious. Surely you can change up the seasoning as you wish.

name: restaurant teriyaki sauce
review: Missing something...don't know what. Orange rind, maybe? Was good, though. Will tinker with it.

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: YUMMY!!!! I made the pasta separately and just added it to the bowls as my kids eat at a different time than my husband and I do and I didn't want soggy noodles. Definitely making this again.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: I tried this recipe last night as a change of pace from our usual soy sauce based marinade for salmon. I loved it. What more can I say? Light. Did not cover up the salmon....thanks for the great recipe.

name: chicken tortilla soup ii
review: Loved the flavor in this soup!  This one pushed out my previous recipe for Tortilla soup.  Thanks!

name: oatmeal cottage cheese pancakes
review: These were super easy. I used 2 whole eggs instead of 4 egg whites. They were a little bland alone but once I poured on some maple syrup my kids gobbled them up!

name: banana chocolate chip muffins
review: Nice batter. Got a nice smooth batter by putting my bananas through a potato ricer. Be warned: baking for 30 minutes is WAY too long! I checked mine at 21 minutes and they were too dark. I'd say 18 minutes would be a better recommendation. I'm going to add a dash of cinnamon next time.

name: weight watchers broccoli cheese soup   2 pts per cup
review: This was quite good.  I cooked some carrots first then added the other things.  My kids couldn't even tell that there were diced tomatoes in this...they thought they were red peppers (bwahahaha)!

name: best oatmeal cookies
review: Perfect texture! Crunchy on the outside, soft and chewey on the inside!

name: 100  whole grain wheat bread
review: We made this for my grandson who is allergic to eggs and dairy products.  We all were very pleased with the texture and taste.  Thanks for sharing.

name: kittencal s marinara pasta sauce  vegetarian
review: This made a lovely, rich, thick sauce and we really liked the flavour. I left out the red wine and crushed red pepper flakes as our toddler was having some but it still had a good flavour to it. Really easy to make too! I didn't feel the need to add sugar and cut the oil to 2tbsp so it was Weight Watcher friendly too. A good all-rounder!

name: olive garden pasta e fagioli soup in a crock pot  copycat
review: We really enjoyed it.  The pot was very nearly too small.  I used a "cheesy" pasta sauce, which I think added a dimension to the flavor.  I'll add more vegetables next time, but otherwise we'll make this again, and again.<br/><br/>Top with Romano, and some toasted bread on the side.  Divine.

name: copycat recipe for carrabba s chicken marsala
review: Fantastic and so easy to make! I didn't use very much shallots, since I'm sensitive, but it still was very flavorful.

name: 24k carrots
review: We really enjoyed this recipe.  I have made it twice now, first with brown sugar and the second time with maple syrup sugar!  Both were a hit with everyone.  Thanks.

name: oven fried chicken chimichangas
review: I made these to take over to a friend who just had a baby. I ended up folding them all, securing with toothpicks and freezing so she could pop one in the oven whenever she needed. The toothpicks can stay in while baking to hold the shape. It worked really well and she absolutely loved them! Thanks for the recipel

name: crazy crust pizza
review: This is the weirdest recipe I have ever seen but it worked! Made when my 3 older grandkids were over and it was very tasty. It fed 5 of us and I think they would have eaten more if there had been any extra. Even my husband went back for 2nd's and he doesn't even like pizza. Will make this again. Thanks for posting!

name: kittencal s parmesan garlic bread or garlic toast
review: Very good. We reduced the amount of parmesan for our taste.

name: perfect pork tenderloin
review: The meat was dry even though I followed the instructions exactly.

name: kale chips
review: Oh my gosh, these are so good!! I used the prepackaged kale and probably only used 1 bunch. I took them out before they were all completely crisped up because I loved the taste. I didn't salt them in the bowl but shook out some kosher salt trying not to overdue it. Was still pretty salty for me, so next time I will just sprinkle a small amount over the pan after I spread it out. A keeper!! Thanks so much for posting!

name: easy cole slaw
review: Not having much of a sweet tooth, I used about a teaspoon of sugar (and don't think I even needed to add that).  I think I would halve the dressing ingredients the next time as there was a tad too much dressing for my tastes.  Great tasting though!

name: christmas rum balls or bourbon balls
review: I finally made these.  I had bought the vanilla wafers before Christmas to make these for the cookie trays but didn't have time to make them.  I didn't have any spiced rum so I used half Bacardi and half Rum Chata.  The dough is very sticky to work with so I used my small scoop to make the balls.  Using the scoop, I made 48 balls.  I used quite a bit more powdered sugar (probably at least half a cup) because I didn't want them to stick to each other.  I already tasted one and it was very good.  I think that the Rum Chata might be less potent than regular rum.  That's okay, I'll just eat two instead of one.  :)  Thank you for posting this recipe!  I'll make sure that I make them for the cookie trays next year!

name: best ever banana cake with cream cheese frosting
review: Rhonda J: I'm breaking my review into two units-1) reviewing how you wrote the recipe, and 2) the end results. First, 1) Your recipe has to be one of the finest, best written and most detailed recipes I've ever had the pleasure of reading!!! How I wish EVERY recipe was this thorough! Not only did you mention bowl size (major props on that point!) but also repeated the ingredients in each step, as cookbooks of old, did. I write out my recipes the exact same way so I truly appreciate the detail and time it took you to post this. 2) End results? Perfect! Incredible! BEST banana cake I've EVER eaten!!!! Followed everything to the letter (did sneak in 1 tsp of Vietnamese Cinnamon). NEVER had over-flow from 9" x 13" pan; mine was done, to perfection in one hour flat! Had no room in freezer but breezeway was at 38 degrees so I set the pan out there, to cool.Used a modified version of your cream cheese frosting; only 2 cups of powdered sugar vs. the amount you posted. Makes for a less sweet frosting and more "cream cheesey". My friends and family were over-the-moon for this cake, so I thank YOU for posting it! Job well done, Rhonda J!!!!

name: parmesan crusted tilapia
review: Loved it, and the parm crispies were a nice bonus.

name: bacardi rum cake
review: What can I say that hasn't been said. Truly yummie. I made 5 cakes. I gave 4 away as gifts. I used  pecans and Bacardi Gold Rum. It was very good. I plan on making this cake every Christman from now on. I also use a Duncun Hines yellow cake mix and added the pudding.

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: The first time I made these I didn't like the lemon  pepper. I made these again without recalling I had made them before and by some stroke of luck forgot the lemon pepper totally, and felt they were perfect with just salt and black pepper. So if someone doesn't like the lemon pepper, try it again without and I'm sure you will love it!

name: crispy ginger beef
review: My boyfriend made this recipe for our dinner.  He made it as written and normally cooks quite well.<br/><br/>I took two bites and my stomach is still aching from the overuse of ginger and crushed red pepper.  It went into the trash.  <br/><br/>I hate that we wasted good beef on this.

name: the best easy beef and broccoli stir fry
review: Definitely a keeper. Super easy. Super tasty. The ginger and the brown sugar really make this dish stand out. I added a little water to make it more saucy.

name: pork chops yum yum
review: I made the recipe as directed and was really disappointed.  The pork chops were inedible until we grabbed a bottle of barbecue sauce for dipping.  The pork chops were REALLY dry.  The sauce did not stick to the chops.  The sauce was thin and watery and pooled in the bottom of the baking dish. I would not make the recipe again without some of the tweaks suggested in the reviews.  Next time I will try covering it in the oven, or pan frying  I also like the idea of some way to thicken the sauce.  My advice is, don't make as the recipe directs but instead follow some of the suggestions in the reviews.

name: monastery lentils
review: Loved this for meatless Mon.  Added about 2/3 c. brown and wild rice I already had as a leftover.<br/>Served with rye bread and Farmers Market Kale salad.

name: delicious chicken pot pie
review: Great flavour, overall a beautiful warming, hearty meal.

name: chicago italian beef
review: BOMB!!! This recipe is great for sandwiches and beef goes so well with rice too! I cooked the beef for 12 hours and it's already fork tender and so so delicious! I made two small changes - 1) I used fresh carrots, broccoli and mushrooms instead of giardiniera; 2) Sweet green pepper was substituted by mini sweet pepper. I wish I could give this recipe 10 stars! The juice softened my french bread. I am not a big sandwich fan, but I devoured this one!

name: caramelized chicken wings
review: The day I made this, the flavor was really good, but the next day the leftovers tasted AMAZING! From now on, if serving this for entertaining, I'll make the day before and reheat.

name: strawberry cheesecake trifle
review: I used low fat versions of the cream cheese and sour cream and used some stevia to replace half of the sugar. I also had to use white cake.  Even with all of these substitutions, it still turned out fantastic.  My only suggestion is not to make this ahead of time.  The cake can get soggy and isn't nearly as good.

name: french bread rolls to die for
review: Fantastic!!!  So easy!!!!  Great taste!!!  I will never buy store bought rolls again.  Thank you for sharing.  A side note - 1 1/2 cups water in microwave for one minute brings water to the right temp to activate the yeast.

name: japanese mum s chicken
review: Enjoyed by the family, great tasting glaze, however a bit time consuming waiting for it to caremalise.

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: We made this for breakfast yesterday and we have had it for 3 meals with just 2 of us.  I have really craving potatoes and onions.  These were great!  Made for Favorites of 2014.

name: yummy crispy baked fish
review: The coating is wonderful - really sticks well. I didn't have any trouble turning it over. I ran out of cayenne, and it really needed it. We ended up needing some tartar sauce.

name: absolute best ever lasagna
review: Super yummy and easy to make.   We made it using just hot Italian sausages and it was still super meaty and decadent.   I used no boil lasagna noodles and it turned out perfect.

name: ground turkey chili for people who hate ground turkey
review: This was OK.  Just not my favorite.  To be fair, I'm not a ground turkey fan to begin with but the title gave me hope.  Sorry.

name: crazy crust pizza
review: I was skeptical that this could be any good, especially after putting the uncooked batter in the oven,  but I was so wrong. It tasted great to me. We did a veggie pizza and after reading some of the other reviews I decided to par-bake the crust for 5 mins before putting the veggies on, cooked for 20 mins, topped with 1 cup of homemade thick sauce and baked about another 10 mins. I baked mine on a foil lined tin and wont use foil next time. The edges were nice and crisp, but the center was still a little soft . It's not pizza crust, but with the toppings it has all the flavors and you can eat it like pizza. I love that I didn't feel grossly full after eating three slices. Thanks for sharing this fun recipe, I'll be making it again.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: These were really delicious and super easy!  I used a full 2 lbs of ground beef (because I'm cheap) and used fresh grated parmesan but followed all of the other ingredients as written.  When it came time to cook the meatball I opted for the oven method and layered in Ragu sauce with the meatballs and baked for 35 minutes.  The came out perfectly cooked and still so moist after cooking.  We used your wonderful meatball recipe to make meatball subs and I plan to use the sauce left in the bottom of the pan to make baked spaghetti casserole tomorrow night.  Thanks for a keep Kittencal!

name: roasted brussels sprouts
review: Now I understand why this recipe has so many 5 star reviews. WOW. This is really great. I used small sprouts so I didn't cut them in half the way I normally do, and I only shook the pan once about 2/3 into the cooking time. I loved the almost burned spots that gave the sprouts so much flavor. I didn't add any extra kosher salt at the end as they were plenty salty already. I would definitely taste them first before adding it or even cut down the salt in half if you don't love salt. Will definitely make this one again!

name: easy cole slaw
